</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Admission </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Stockholders or their legal proxy holders may attend the Annual Meeting. Due to space constraints and other security considerations, we are not able to
admit the guests of either stockholders or their legal proxy holders. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt" BGCOLOR="#dee3ee">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="center"><B>Important Notice Regarding Admission to the 2017 Annual Meeting</B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.63em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Stockholders or their legal proxy holders who wish
to attend the Annual Meeting must preregister with and obtain an admission ticket from Chevron&#146;s Corporate Governance Department. Tickets will be distributed on a first-come, first-served basis. Requests for admission tickets must be received
by Chevron no later than 5:00 p.m. PDT on Thursday, May&nbsp;25, 2017. For complete instructions for preregistering and obtaining an admission ticket, see page 81 of this Proxy Statement.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#dee3ee" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt" BGCOLOR="#dee3ee"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Voting </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Stockholders owning Chevron common stock at the close of business on Monday, April&nbsp;3, 2017, or their legal proxy holders, are entitled to vote at the
Annual Meeting. Please refer to pages 1 through 3 of this Proxy Statement for information about voting at the Annual Meeting. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Distribution
of Proxy Materials </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">On Tuesday, April&nbsp;11, 2017, we will commence distributing to our stockholders (1)&nbsp;a copy of this Proxy
Statement, a proxy card or voting instruction form, and our Annual Report (the Proxy Materials), (2)&nbsp;a Notice Regarding the Availability of Proxy Materials, with instructions to access our Proxy Materials and vote on the Internet, or
(3)&nbsp;for stockholders who receive materials electronically, an email with instructions to access our Proxy Materials and vote on the Internet. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="right">By
Order of the Board of Directors, </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="right">


<IMG SRC="g304635g25m15.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="right"><B>Mary A. Francis </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="right"><I>Corporate Secretary and Chief Governance Officer </I></P>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="justify"><B>Chevron Corporation </B></P>

</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Your Board of Directors is providing you with these Proxy Materials in connection with its solicitation of proxies to be voted at Chevron
Corporation&#146;s 2017 Annual Meeting of Stockholders to be held on Wednesday, May&nbsp;31, 2017, at 8:00 a.m. CDT at Chevron U.S.A., Inc., 6301 Deauville Boulevard, Midland, Texas, and at any postponement or adjournment of the Annual Meeting. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">In this Proxy Statement, Chevron and its subsidiaries may also be referred to as &#147;we,&#148; &#147;our,&#148; &#147;the Company,&#148; or &#147;the
Corporation.&#148; </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B><A NAME="xtoc304635_2"></A>Items of Business </B></FONT></P>

not vote your shares, your bank, broker, or other holder of record can vote your shares at its discretion ONLY on Item&nbsp;2. If you do not give your bank, broker, or other holder of record instructions on how to vote your shares on Item&nbsp;1 or
Items 3 through 11, your shares will not be voted on those matters. If you have shares in an employee stock or retirement benefit plan and do not vote those shares, the plan trustee or fiduciary may or may not vote your shares, in accordance with
the terms of the plan. Any shares not voted on Item&nbsp;1 or Items 3 through 11 (whether by abstention, broker nonvote, or otherwise) will have no impact on that particular item. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:3pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">We are not aware of any matters that are expected to be presented for a vote at the Annual Meeting other than those described above. If any other matter
should properly be brought before the Annual Meeting by or at the direction of the Board, the proxy holders identified in the &#147;Voting Information&#151;Appointment of Proxy Holders&#148; section of this Proxy Statement intend to vote the proxies
in accordance with their best judgment. When conducting the Annual Meeting, the Chairman or his designee may refuse to allow a vote on any matter not made in compliance with our By-Laws and the procedures described in the &#147;Additional
Information&#151;Submission of Stockholder Proposals for 2017 Annual Meeting&#148; section of the 2016 Proxy Statement. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B><A NAME="xtoc304635_3">
</A>Vote Results </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:16pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">At the Annual Meeting, we will announce preliminary vote results for those items of business properly presented. Within
four business days of the Annual Meeting, we will disclose the preliminary results (or final results, if available) in a Current Report on Form 8-K filed with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission. </P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><A NAME="xtoc304635_4"></A><B>Appointment of Proxy Holders</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:16pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Your Board asks you to appoint John S. Watson, R. Hewitt Pate, and Mary A. Francis as your proxy holders,
each with full power of substitution, to represent and to vote your shares at the Annual Meeting. You make this appointment by voting the proxy card provided to you using one of the voting methods described in &#147;How to Vote&#148; in this
section. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">If you sign and return a proxy card with voting instructions, the proxy holders will vote your shares as you direct on the matters
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
described in this Proxy Statement. If you sign and return a proxy card without voting instructions, they will vote your shares as recommended by your Board. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Unless you indicate otherwise on the proxy card, you also authorize the proxy holders to vote your shares on any matters that are not known by your Board
as of the date of this Proxy Statement and that may be properly presented by or at the direction of the Board for action at the Annual Meeting.
</P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:24pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><A NAME="xtoc304635_5"></A><B>Record Date; Who Can Vote</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:16pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Stockholders owning Chevron common stock at the close of business on Monday, April&nbsp;3, 2017, the Record Date, or their legal proxy holders, are
entitled to vote at the Annual Meeting. At the close of business on the Record Date, there were 1,894,561,619 shares of Chevron common stock outstanding. Each outstanding share of Chevron common stock is entitled to one vote. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><A NAME="xtoc304635_6"></A><B>Quorum</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:16pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">A quorum, which is a majority of the outstanding shares of Chevron common stock as of the Record Date, must be present to hold the Annual Meeting. A
quorum is calculated based on the number of shares represented at the meeting, either by the stockholders attending in person or by the proxy holders. If you indicate an abstention as your voting preference in any matter, your shares will be counted
toward a quorum, but will not be voted on any such matter. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><A NAME="xtoc304635_7"></A><B>How to Vote</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:16pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Stockholders can vote by mail, telephone, Internet, or in person at the Annual Meeting. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" ALIGN="center">

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>

your own name as reflected in the records of Chevron&#146;s transfer agent, Computershare Shareowner Services LLC, you can most conveniently vote by&nbsp;telephone, Internet, or mail. Please review the voting instructions on&nbsp;your proxy
card.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">If you vote by telephone or on the Internet, you do not need to return your proxy card.
Telephone and Internet voting are available 24 hours a day and will close&nbsp;at 11:59 p.m. EDT on Tuesday, May&nbsp;30, 2017.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">You can vote in person at the Annual Meeting by completing, signing, dating, and returning your proxy card during the meeting.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">If you own your shares through a bank, broker, or other holder of record, you
can&nbsp;most conveniently vote by telephone, Internet, or mail. Please review the voting instructions on your voting instruction form.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">If you vote by telephone or on the Internet, you do not need to return your voting instruction form. Telephone and Internet voting are available 24 hours a day and will
close at 11:59 p.m. EDT on Tuesday, May&nbsp;30, 2017.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">You can vote in person at the Annual
Meeting ONLY if you obtain and present a proxy, executed in your favor, from the bank, broker, or other holder of record of your shares.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>

employee stock or retirement benefit plan, you can most conveniently vote by telephone, Internet, or mail. Please review the voting instructions contained in the email sent to your work address or in the materials you receive through the mail.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">All votes must be received by the plan trustee or fiduciary by 11:59 p.m. EDT on Thursday, May 25,
2017, or other cutoff date as determined by the&nbsp;plan trustee or fiduciary.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">You can vote in
person at the Annual Meeting ONLY if you obtain and present a proxy, executed in your favor, from the trustee or fiduciary of the plan through which you hold your&nbsp;shares.</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial"><B>We encourage you to vote by telephone or on the Internet.</B></FONT><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial"> Both are designed to record your vote immediately and enable you to confirm that your vote has been properly recorded. </FONT></P>

<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP ALIGN="right" BGCOLOR="#284993"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#ffffff">&nbsp;&nbsp;VOTING&nbsp;INFORMATION&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><A NAME="xtoc304635_8"></A><B>Revoking Your Proxy or Voting Instructions</B>
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:16pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Stockholders can revoke their proxy or voting instructions as follows. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="46%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="25%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="25%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><B>Stockholders of Record</B></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000"><B>Street Name Stockholders</B></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"><B>Employee Plan Participants</B></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.25em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Send a written statement revoking your proxy to: Chevron Corporation, Attn: Corporate Secretary and Chief Governance Officer, 6001 Bollinger Canyon Road, San Ramon, CA 94583-2324;</P></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ROWSPAN="4" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000">Notify your bank, broker, or other holder of record in accordance with that entity&#146;s procedures for revoking your voting
instructions.</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ROWSPAN="4" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">Notify the trustee or fiduciary of the plan through which you hold your shares in accordance with its procedures for revoking
your voting instructions.</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.25em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Submit a proxy card with a later date and signed as your name appears on your account;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.25em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Vote at a later time by telephone or&nbsp;the&nbsp;Internet; or</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">
<P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.25em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Vote in person at the Annual Meeting.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><A NAME="xtoc304635_9"></A><B>Confidential Voting</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:16pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Chevron has a confidential voting policy to protect the privacy of your votes. Under this policy, ballots,
proxy cards, and voting instructions returned to banks, brokers, and other holders of record are kept confidential. Only the proxy solicitor, the proxy tabulator, and the Inspector of Election have access to the ballots, proxy cards, and voting
instructions. Anyone who processes or
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
inspects the ballots, proxy cards, and voting instructions signs a pledge to treat them as confidential. None of these persons is a Chevron Director, officer, or employee. The proxy solicitor and
the proxy tabulator will disclose information taken from the ballots, proxy cards, and voting instructions only in the event of a proxy contest or as otherwise required by law.
</P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="96%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%"></TD></TR>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B><SUB STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:bottom"></SUB></B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993"><I>Chevron Corporation&#151;2017 Proxy Statement</I></FONT><FONT
 COLOR="#284993"><B></B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">3</TD></TR></TABLE>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:20pt">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="91%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:20pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5e5e5"> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:20pt; font-family:Arial"><B><A NAME="xtoc304635_10"></A>Election of Directors</B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:20pt; font-family:Arial"><I><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">(Item 1 on the&nbsp;Proxy Card)</FONT></I></P> <P STYLE="font-size:16pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Your Board is nominating the 12 individuals identified for election as Directors. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Directors are elected annually and serve for a one-year term or until their successors are elected. If any nominee is unable to serve as a Director&#151;a
circumstance we do not anticipate&#151;the Board by resolution may reduce the number of Directors or choose a substitute. Your Board has determined that each non-employee Director is independent in accordance with the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE)
Corporate Governance Standards and that no material relationship exists that would interfere with the exercise of independent judgment in carrying out the responsibilities of a Director. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B><A NAME="xtoc304635_11"></A>Director Election Requirements </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:16pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Each Director nominee who receives a majority of the votes cast (i.e., the number of shares voted FOR a
Director nominee must exceed the number of shares voted AGAINST that Director nominee, excluding abstentions) will be elected a Director, in an uncontested election. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Under Chevron&#146;s By-Laws, in an uncontested election any Director nominee who receives more AGAINST votes than FOR votes must submit an offer of
resignation to the Board. The&nbsp;Board
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
Nominating and Governance Committee must then consider all relevant facts and circumstances, including the Director&#146;s qualifications and past and expected future contributions, the overall
composition of the Board, and whether Chevron would meet regulatory or similar requirements without the Director, and make a recommendation to the Board on the action to take with respect to the offer of resignation.
</P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:24pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B><A NAME="xtoc304635_12"></A>Director Qualifications and Nomination Processes </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:16pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The Board Nominating and Governance Committee (the Committee) is responsible for recommending to the Board
the qualifications for Board membership and for identifying, assessing, and recommending qualified Director candidates for the Board&#146;s consideration. The Board membership qualifications and nomination procedures are set forth in Chevron&#146;s
Corporate Governance Guidelines, which are available on our website at <I>www.chevron.com</I>. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><div style="width:100%;margin-left:0%; margin-right:0%;border:solid 1px;background-color:#d8d8d8;padding-top:2pt;padding-bottom:3pt">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-top:0pt; margin-left:5pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="justify"><B>All Directors should have the following attributes: </B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="9">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">the highest professional and personal ethics and values, consistent with The Chevron Way and our Business Conduct and
Ethics Code, both of which are available on Chevron&#146;s website at <I>www.chevron.com</I>; </P></TD>
<TD WIDTH="6">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="9">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">a commitment to building stockholder value; </P></TD>
<TD WIDTH="6">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="9">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">business acumen and broad experience and expertise at the policy-making level in one or more of the areas of particular
consideration indicated below; </P></TD>
<TD WIDTH="6">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="9">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">the ability to provide insights and practical wisdom based on the individual&#146;s experience or expertise; </P></TD>
<TD WIDTH="6">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="9">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">sufficient time to effectively carry out duties as a Director; and </P></TD>
<TD WIDTH="6">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="9">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">independence (at least a majority of the Board must consist of independent Directors, as defined by the NYSE Corporate
Governance Standards). </P></TD>
<TD WIDTH="6">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></div> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The Committee uses a skills and qualifications matrix to ensure that the Board maintains a balance of
knowledge and experience. The Committee regularly reviews the appropriate skills and characteristics required of Directors in the context of the current composition of the Board, the operating requirements of the Company, and the long-term interests
of stockholders. </P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <div style="width:100%;margin-left:0%; margin-right:0%;border:solid 1px;background-color:#d8d8d8;padding-top:2pt;padding-bottom:3pt">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-top:0pt; margin-left:5pt; margin-right:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="justify"><B>When conducting its review of the appropriate skills and qualifications desired of Directors, the
Committee particularly considers: </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="9">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">leadership experience in business as a chief executive officer, senior executive, or leader of significant business
operations; </P></TD>
<TD WIDTH="6">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="9">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">expertise in science, technology, engineering, research, or academia; </P></TD>
<TD WIDTH="6">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="9">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">extensive knowledge of governmental, regulatory, legal, or public policy issues; </P></TD>
<TD WIDTH="6">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="9">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">expertise in finance, financial disclosure, or financial accounting; </P></TD>
<TD WIDTH="6">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="9">&nbsp;</TD>

<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">experience in global business or international matters; </P></TD>
<TD WIDTH="6">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="9">&nbsp;</TD>

<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>

<TD WIDTH="6">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="9">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">service as a public company director; </P></TD>
<TD WIDTH="6">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="9">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">diversity of age, gender, and ethnicity; and </P></TD>
<TD WIDTH="6">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="9">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">such other factors as the Committee deems appropriate, given the current needs of the Board and the Company, to maintain
a balance of knowledge, experience, background, and capability.</P></TD>
<TD WIDTH="6">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></div> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The Committee considers Director candidates suggested for nomination to the Board from stockholders,
Directors, and other sources. Directors periodically suggest possible candidates, and from time to time, the Committee may engage a third-party consultant to assist in identifying potential candidates. The Committee has retained Russell Reynolds
Associates to assist it with identifying potential candidates. Russell Reynolds has interviewed current Directors, evaluated the Board&#146;s current and future makeup and needs, and worked with the Committee to develop a list of potential
candidates. </P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">

Statement</I></FONT><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B></B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

 <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><div style="width:100%;margin-left:0%; margin-right:0%;border:solid 1px;background-color:#d8d8d8;padding-top:2pt;padding-bottom:3pt">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-top:0pt; margin-left:5pt; margin-right:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="justify"><B>The Committee considers all potential nominees recommended by our stockholders. </B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Stockholders may recommend potential nominees by writing to the Corporate Secretary at 6001 Bollinger Canyon Road, San
Ramon, CA 94583-2324, stating the candidate&#146;s name and qualifications for Board membership. </P></TD>
<TD WIDTH="6">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">When considering potential nominees recommended by stockholders, the Committee follows the same Board membership
qualifications evaluation and nomination procedures discussed in this section.</P></TD>
<TD WIDTH="6">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></div></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">In addition, a qualifying stockholder (or stockholders) may nominate director nominees for inclusion in our
Proxy Statement if the nominating stockholder satisfies the requirements specified in our proxy access By-Laws, which are described in the &#147;Additional Information&#151;Submission of Stockholder Proposals for 2018 Annual Meeting&#148; section of
this Proxy Statement. </P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:1pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:23pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B><A NAME="xtoc304635_13"></A>Nominees for Director </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:16pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">For the 2017 Annual Meeting, the Committee recommended and the Board concurred with a Board size of 12 Directors.&nbsp;Each of the Director nominees is a
current Director. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:14pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993">Your Board recommends that you vote FOR each of these Director nominees. </FONT></P>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Dr.&nbsp;Austin</B></FONT><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993"> has held an adjunct Research Professor appointment at the University of Southern California&#146;s Viterbi School&#146;s Department of Industrial and Systems Engineering since 2007. She served as President
and Chief Executive Officer of The Aerospace Corporation, a leading architect for the United States&#146; national security space programs, from 2008 until her retirement in 2016. From 2004 to 2007, she was Senior Vice President, National Systems
Group at Aerospace. Dr.&nbsp;Austin joined Aerospace in 1979. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.5pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="justify"><B>Skills and Qualifications </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial"><B><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993">Business Leadership / Operations:</FONT> </B></FONT><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial">Eight years as CEO of The Aerospace Corporation. Thirty-seven-year career with The Aerospace Corporation included numerous senior management and executive positions. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Finance: </B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">Over a decade of financial responsibility and
experience at The Aerospace Corporation. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Global Business / International
Affairs:</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial"> Internationally recognized for her work in satellite and payload system acquisition, systems engineering and system simulation. Former CEO of a company that provides space systems expertise to
international organizations. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Government / Regulatory / Public Policy:</B></FONT><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial"> Served on President&#146;s Council of Advisors on Science and Technology and President&#146;s Review of U.S. Human Space Flight Plans Committee. Appointed to the Defense Science Board and the NASA Advisory Council.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Research / Academia: </B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">Research Professor at the
University of Southern California&#146;s Viterbi School of Engineering. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Science /
Technology / Engineering: </B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">PhD in Industrial and Systems Engineering from the University of Southern California, Master of Science in both Systems Engineering and Mathematics from the University of
Pittsburgh. Thirty-seven-year career in national security space programs. Fellow of the American Institute of Aeronautics and Astronautics. </FONT></P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.23em; text-indent:-0.92em; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Houston Endowment, Inc.</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.23em; text-indent:-0.92em; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Houston Museum of Fine Arts</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.23em; text-indent:-0.92em; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;University of Texas MD Anderson Cancer Center Board of
Visitors</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Ms. Deily</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993">
served as Deputy U.S. Trade Representative and U.S. Ambassador to the World Trade Organization (WTO) from 2001 until 2005. She was Vice Chairman of Charles Schwab Corporation, a brokerage and financial services company, from 2000 until 2001,
President of Schwab Retail Group from 1998 until 2000, and President of Schwab Institutional Services for Investment Managers from 1996 until 1998. Prior to joining Schwab, Ms.&nbsp;Deily was Chairman, Chief Executive Officer, and President from
1990 until 1996 and President and Chief Operating Officer from 1988 until 1990 of First Interstate Bank of Texas. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.5pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="justify"><B>Skills and Qualifications </B></P>

Charles Schwab; President, Schwab Retail Group; and President, Schwab Institutional Services for Investment Managers.&nbsp;Former Chairman, CEO, President, and COO, First Interstate Bank of Texas. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:4pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Environmental Affairs:</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial"> As Deputy U.S. Trade Representative
and U.S. Ambassador to the WTO, oversaw negotiation of various environmental issues. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:4pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Finance:</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial"> More than 20 years of experience in the banking and
financial services industry. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:4pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Global Business / International Affairs:</B></FONT><FONT

<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Dr.&nbsp;Gast</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993"> has been President of
Imperial College London, a public research university specializing in science, engineering, medicine, and business, since 2014. She was President of Lehigh University, a private research university, from 2006 until 2014 and Vice President for
Research, Associate Provost, and Robert T. Haslam Chair in Chemical Engineering at Massachusetts Institute of Technology from 2001 until 2006. Dr.&nbsp;Gast was professor of chemical engineering at Stanford University and the Stanford Synchrotron
Radiation Laboratory from 1985 until 2001. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.5pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="justify"><B>Skills and Qualifications </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Environmental Affairs: </B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">At Imperial College London, oversees environmental institutes and centers and leads the university crisis management group. At Lehigh
University, presided over environmental centers, advisory groups, and crisis management. Expertise in chemical and biological terrorism issues gained through service on several governmental committees. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Finance: </B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">Eleven years of service as president of leading
educational institutions, with ultimate responsibility for finance, fundraising, and endowment management. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Global Business / International Affairs: </B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">Served as a U.S. Science Envoy for the U.S. Department of State to advise on ways to foster and deepen relationships
with the Caucasus and Central Asia. Serves on the Singapore Ministry of Education&#146;s Academic Research Council and on the Board of Trustees for the King Abdullah University of Science and Technology in Saudi Arabia. Serves on the Global
Federation of Competitiveness Councils and on the Global Science and Innovation Advisory Council to the Prime Minister of Malaysia. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Government / Regulatory / Public Policy:</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial"> Served on the Homeland Security Science and Technology Advisory Committee.&nbsp;Chaired the scientific review committee
empaneled by the National Research Council at the request of the FBI to conduct an independent review of the investigatory methods used by the FBI in the criminal case involving the mailing of anthrax spores. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Research / Academia: </B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">More than three decades of service in
academia and research at leading educational institutions. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Science / Technology /
Engineering:</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial"> M.A. and Ph.D. in chemical engineering from Princeton University.&nbsp;Former Vice President for Research, Associate Provost, and Robert T. Haslam Chair in Chemical Engineering at Massachusetts
Institute of Technology and professor of chemical engineering at Stanford University and the Stanford Synchrotron Radiation Laboratory. </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:Arial"><B>Chairman, Chief Executive Officer and President, Inter-Con Security Systems, Inc.</B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Mr.&nbsp;Hernandez </B></FONT><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993">has been Chairman, Chief Executive Officer, and President of Inter-Con Security Systems, Inc., a global provider of security and facility support services to governments, utilities, and industrial customers,
since 1986. He was Executive Vice President and Assistant General Counsel of Inter-Con from 1984 until 1986 and an associate of the law firm of Brobeck, Phleger&nbsp;&amp; Harrison from 1980 until 1984. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.5pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="justify"><B>Skills and Qualifications </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Business Leadership / Operations: </B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">Three decades of service as CEO of Inter-Con Security Systems, Inc. Co-founder of Interspan Communications, a television
broadcasting company. Chairman of the Board of McDonald&#146;s Corporation. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Finance:
</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">Three decades of financial responsibility and experience at Inter-Con Security Systems, Inc. Chaired the audit committee at McDonald&#146;s Corporation. Chair of the finance committee and risk committee at
Wells Fargo&nbsp;&amp; Company. Former audit committee member at Great Western Financial Corporation, Nordstrom, Inc., Washington Mutual, Inc., and Wells Fargo&nbsp;&amp; Company. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Global Business / International Affairs:</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial"> CEO of a company
that conducts business worldwide.&nbsp;Director of companies with international operations. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Government / Regulatory / Public Policy:</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial"> Trustee of the John
Randolph Haynes Foundation, which has funded hundreds of important urban studies in education, transportation, local government elections, public safety, and other public issues. Former appointee and Commissioner and President of the Los Angeles
Police Commission.&nbsp;Served on the U.S. National Infrastructure Advisory Committee. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Legal:</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial"> Served as EVP and Assistant General Counsel of
Inter-Con Security Systems.&nbsp;Former litigation associate of the law firm of Brobeck, Phleger&nbsp;&amp; Harrison.&nbsp;Law degree from Harvard Law School. </FONT></P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;U.S. Naval Academy Foundation</P>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Governor Huntsman</B></FONT><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993"> has been Chairman of the Atlantic Council, a nonprofit that promotes leadership and engagement in international affairs, since 2014 and Chairman of the Huntsman Cancer Foundation, a nonprofit organization
that financially supports research, education, and patient care initiatives at Huntsman Cancer Institute at the University of Utah, since 2012. He was a candidate for the Republican nomination for president of the United States in 2011. Governor
Huntsman served as U.S. Ambassador to China from 2009 until 2011 and two consecutive terms as Governor of Utah from 2005 until 2009. Prior to his service as Governor, he served as U.S. Ambassador to Singapore, Deputy U.S. Trade Representative, and
Deputy Assistant Secretary of Commerce for Asia. Between these appointments, Governor Huntsman was employed by Huntsman Corporation, a global manufacturer and marketer of differentiated chemicals, in various capacities, including Vice Chairman, and
as Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Huntsman Holdings Corporation, until his resignation in 2005. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.5pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="justify"><B>Skills and Qualifications </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Business Leadership / Operations: </B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">Served eight years as
Vice Chairman of Huntsman Corporation and Chairman and CEO of Huntsman Holdings Corporation. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Environmental Affairs: </B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">As Governor of Utah, oversaw
environmental policy, including signing the Western Climate Initiative, by which Utah joined with other U.S. state governments to pursue targets for reduced greenhouse gas emissions.&nbsp;Significant experience overseeing environmental practices and
related matters as Vice Chairman of Huntsman Corporation and Chairman and CEO of Huntsman Holdings Corporation. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Finance: </B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">Former executive officer of Huntsman Corporation and Huntsman Holdings Corporation. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Global Business / International Affairs:</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial"> Chairman of the
Atlantic Council.&nbsp;Trustee of the National Committee on US-China Relations and of the Carnegie Endowment for International Peace.&nbsp;Former U.S. Ambassador to China.&nbsp;Former two-term Governor of Utah.&nbsp;Former U.S. Ambassador to
Singapore, Deputy U.S. Trade Representative, and Deputy Assistant Secretary of Commerce for Asia.&nbsp;Founding director of the Pacific Council on International Policy.&nbsp;Current and former director of companies with international operations.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Government / Regulatory / Public Policy:</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial"> Former
two-term Governor of Utah.&nbsp;Former Deputy U.S. Trade Representative and Deputy Assistant Secretary of Commerce for Asia.&nbsp;Co-Chair of No-Labels, a nonprofit organization that works across political party lines to reduce gridlock and create
policy solutions. </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Mr.&nbsp;Moorman</B></FONT><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993"> has been the President and Chief Executive Officer of Amtrak, a passenger rail service provider since September 2016. He was previously Chairman from 2006, and Chief Executive Officer from 2004, of Norfolk
Southern Corporation, a freight and transportation company until his retirement in 2015. He served as President of Norfolk Southern from 2004 until 2013. Prior to that, Mr.&nbsp;Moorman was Senior Vice President of Corporate Planning and Services
from 2003 until 2004 and Senior Vice President of Corporate Services in 2003. Mr.&nbsp;Moorman joined Norfolk Southern in 1975. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.5pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="justify"><B>Skills and Qualifications </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Business Leadership / Operations: </B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">Served more than a decade
as CEO of Norfolk Southern Corporation.&nbsp;Forty-year career with Norfolk Southern included numerous senior management and executive positions, with emphasis on operations. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Environmental Affairs:</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial"> At Norfolk Southern Corporation,
gained experience with environmental issues related to transportation of coal, automotive and industrial products.&nbsp;Serves as Virginia chapter chair of The Nature Conservancy, a global conservation organization.&nbsp;Served as a trustee of the
Chesapeake Bay Foundation, whose mission is to protect the environmental integrity of the bay. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Finance: </B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">Former CEO of Fortune 500 company.&nbsp;More than
three decades of financial responsibility and experience at Norfolk Southern Corporation. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Government / Regulatory / Public Policy:</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial"> More than three
decades of experience in the highly regulated freight and transportation industry. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Science
/ Technology / Engineering:</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial"> Forty-year career with Norfolk Southern included numerous senior management and executive positions requiring expertise in engineering and technology.&nbsp;Norfolk Southern
builds and maintains track and bridges, operates trains and equipment, and designs and manages complex information technology systems. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:24pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Dr.&nbsp;Moyo
</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993">has been Chief Executive Officer of Mildstorm since she founded it in 2015, where she is a global economist and commentator analyzing the macroeconomy and international affairs. From 2001 to
2008, she worked at Goldman Sachs in various roles, including as an economist. Prior to that she worked at the World Bank in Washington, D.C. from 1993 until 1995. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.5pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="justify"><B>Skills and Qualifications </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Environmental Affairs:</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial"> As director at Barrick Gold
Corporation, served on the committee that considered and provided oversight on environmental matters. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Finance:</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial"> Ten years of experience at Goldman Sachs and the World Bank. PhD in economics from the University of Oxford and MBA in finance from The&nbsp;American
University. Audit Committee member at Barrick Gold Corporation and Seagate Technology. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Global Business / International Affairs:</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial"> Traveled to more
than 70 countries over the last decade, with a particular focus on the interplay of international business and the global economy, while highlighting key opportunities for investment. Director of companies with international operations. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Government / Regulatory / Public Policy:</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial"> Ten years of
experience in the highly regulated banking and financial services industry. MPA in Public Administration from John F. Kennedy School of Government, Harvard. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Research / Academia: </B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">Author of three New York Times
bestsellers. Writing regularly appears in economic and finance-related publications. </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1.50pt solid #ffffff"> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Ronald D.
Sugar</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:Arial"><B>Retired Chairman and Chief Executive Officer, Northrop Grumman Corporation</B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial"><B>Lead Director since:</B></FONT> 2015</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial"><B>Age:</B></FONT> 68</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial"><B>Director Since:</B></FONT> April 2005</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:arial"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Arial"><B>Independent:</B></FONT> Yes</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:Arial"><B>Chevron&nbsp;Committees:</B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:1pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Board Nominating and Governance (Chair)</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:1pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Management Compensation</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:Arial"><B>Current Public Company Directorships:</B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:1pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Air Lease Corporation</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:1pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Amgen Inc.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:1pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Apple Inc.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1.50pt solid #ffffff">&nbsp;</TD>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:arial">(within last five years):</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;None</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:Arial"><B>Other Directorships and Memberships:</B></P>

<P STYLE="font-size:1pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font-size:1pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Boys&nbsp;&amp; Girls Clubs of America</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:1pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Los Angeles Philharmonic Association</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:1pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;National Academy of Engineering</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:1pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;UCLA Anderson School of Management Board of Visitors</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:1pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;University of Southern California</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Dr.&nbsp;Sugar</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993"> is a senior advisor to
various businesses and organizations, including Ares Management LLC, a leading private investment firm; Bain&nbsp;&amp; Company, a global consulting firm; Temasek Americas Advisory Panel, a private investment company based in Singapore; and the G100
Network and the World 50, peer-to-peer exchanges for current and former senior executives from some of the world&#146;s largest companies. He was previously Chairman and Chief Executive Officer from 2003 until his retirement in 2010 and President
and Chief Operating Officer from 2001 until 2003 of Northrop Grumman Corporation, a global security and defense company. He joined Northrop Grumman in 2001, having previously served as President and Chief Operating Officer of Litton Industries,
Inc., a developer of military products, and earlier as an executive of TRW Inc., a developer of missile systems and spacecraft. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:8pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.5pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="justify"><B>Skills and Qualifications </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Business Leadership / Operations:</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial"> Served seven years as CEO
of Northrop Grumman Corporation.&nbsp;Senior management and executive positions, including service as COO, at Northrop Grumman, Litton Industries, Inc., and TRW Inc. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Environmental Affairs:</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial"> As Chairman, CEO, and President of
Northrop Grumman Corporation, oversaw environmental assessments and remediations at shipyards and aircraft and electronics factories. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Finance:</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial"> Former CFO of Fortune 500 company.&nbsp;More than three decades of financial responsibility and experience at Northrop Grumman, Litton Industries, Inc.,
and TRW Inc.&nbsp;Current audit committee chair at Apple Inc. and former audit committee chair at Chevron. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Global Business / International Affairs:</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial"> Former CEO of Fortune 500 company with extensive international operations.&nbsp;Current and former director of companies
with international operations. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Government / Regulatory / Public Policy:</B></FONT><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial"> At Northrop Grumman Corporation, a key government contractor, oversaw development of weapons and other technologies.&nbsp;Appointed by President of the United States to the National Security Telecommunications Advisory
Committee.&nbsp;Former director of World Affairs Council of Los Angeles. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Science /
Technology / Engineering:</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial"> Ph.D. in electrical engineering from the University of California at Los Angeles.&nbsp;Served in a variety of senior management and executive positions at Northrop Grumman, Litton
Industries, Inc., and TRW Inc., requiring expertise in engineering and technology.&nbsp;Director at Amgen Inc., a biotechnology company; Apple Inc., a manufacturer and seller of, among other things, personal computers, mobile communication, and
media devices; and BeyondTrust, a global cybersecurity company. </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Board Nominating and Governance</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:1pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Management Compensation</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:Arial"><B>Current Public Company Directorships:</B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;3M Company</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:Arial"><B>Prior Public Company Directorships </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:arial">(within last five years):</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;The Toro Company</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:arial"><B>Other Directorships and Memberships:</B></P>
