<TR>
<TD WIDTH="29%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="68%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" NOWRAP STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><B>Committees&nbsp;and&nbsp;Membership</B></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"><B>Committee&nbsp;Functions</B></TD></TR>


<TR BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Audit</B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Charles W. Moorman IV, Chair</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Robert E. Denham</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Jon M. Huntsman Jr.</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Dambisa F. Moyo</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Selects the independent registered public accounting firm for
endorsement by&nbsp;the&nbsp;Board and ratification by the stockholders</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Reviews reports of the independent registered public
accounting firm and internal auditors</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Reviews and approves the scope and cost of all services (including nonaudit services) provided by the independent registered public accounting firm</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Monitors the effectiveness of the audit process and financial
reporting</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Reviews the adequacy of financial and operating controls</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Monitors implementation and effectiveness of Chevron&#146;s
compliance policies and&nbsp;procedures</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Assists the Board in fulfilling its oversight of financial risk as part of Chevron&#146;s broad enterprise risk management program</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Evaluates the effectiveness of the Audit Committee</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Board&nbsp;Nominating&nbsp;and&nbsp;Governance&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Ronald D. Sugar, Chair</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Wanda M. Austin</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Linnet F. Deily</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Alice P. Gast</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Inge G. Thulin</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Evaluates the effectiveness of the Board and its committees
and recommends changes to improve Board, Board committee, and individual Director effectiveness</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Assesses the size and composition of the Board</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Recommends prospective Director nominees</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Reviews and approves non-employee Director compensation</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Reviews and recommends changes as appropriate in
Chevron&#146;s Corporate Governance Guidelines, Restated Certificate of Incorporation, By-Laws, and other Board-adopted governance provisions</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Reviews stockholder proposals and recommends Board responses
to proposals</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Assists the Board in fulfilling its oversight of enterprise
risk management, particularly risks in connection with Chevron&#146;s corporate governance structures and&nbsp;processes</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Evaluates the effectiveness of the Board Nominating and
Governance Committee</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Management Compensation</B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Enrique Hernandez, Jr., Chair</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Robert E. Denham</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Ronald D. Sugar</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Inge G. Thulin</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Conducts an annual review of the CEO&#146;s performance</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Reviews and recommends to the independent Directors the salary
and other compensation for the CEO</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Reviews and approves salaries and other compensation for executive officers other than the CEO</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Administers Chevron&#146;s executive incentive and
equity-based compensation plans</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Reviews Chevron&#146;s strategies and supporting processes for management succession planning, leadership development, executive retention, and diversity</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Assists the Board in fulfilling its oversight of enterprise
risk management, particularly risks in connection with Chevron&#146;s compensation programs</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Evaluates the effectiveness of the Management Compensation
Committee</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Public Policy</B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Linnet F. Deily, Chair</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Wanda M. Austin</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Alice P. Gast</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Enrique Hernandez, Jr.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Identifies, monitors, and evaluates domestic and international social, political, human rights, and environmental trends and issues that affect Chevron&#146;s activities
and&nbsp;performance</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Recommends to the Board policies, programs, and strategies concerning such issues</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Recommends to the Board policies, programs, and practices
concerning support of&nbsp;charitable, political, and educational organizations</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Reviews annually the policies, procedures, and expenditures
for Chevron&#146;s political activities, including political contributions and direct and indirect lobbying</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Reviews stockholder proposals and recommends Board responses
to proposals</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Assists the Board in fulfilling its oversight of enterprise
risk management, particularly risks in connection with the social, political, environmental, and public policy aspects of Chevron&#146;s business</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Evaluates the effectiveness of the Public Policy
Committee</P></TD></TR>

<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP BGCOLOR="#284993"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#ffffff">&nbsp;&nbsp;CORPORATE&nbsp;GOVERNANCE&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD></TR></TABLE> <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B><A NAME="xtoc304635_27"></A>Board and
Committee Meetings and Attendance </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:16pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">In 2016, your Board held six Board meetings, with each meeting including an executive session of
independent Directors presided over by our independent Lead Director, and 24 Board committee meetings, which included nine Audit Committee, six Board Nominating and Governance Committee, five Management Compensation Committee, and four Public Policy
Committee meetings. Chevron&#146;s incumbent directors, on average, attended 94 percent of the Board and Committee meetings during 2016. No director attended less than 75 percent of such meetings.
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
Chevron&#146;s policy regarding Directors&#146; attendance at the Annual Meeting, as described in the &#147;Board Agenda and Meetings&#148; section of Chevron&#146;s Corporate Governance
Guidelines (available at <I>www.chevron.com</I>), is that all Directors are expected to attend the Annual Meeting, absent extenuating circumstances.&nbsp;All current Directors attended the 2016 Annual Meeting, other than Drs. Austin and Moyo, who
joined the Board following the meeting. </P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:24pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B><A NAME="xtoc304635_28"></A>Board and Committee Oversight of Risk </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:16pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">One of the many duties of your Board is to oversee Chevron&#146;s risk management policies and practices to
ensure that the appropriate risk management systems are employed throughout the Company. Chevron faces a broad array of risks, including
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
market, operational, strategic, legal, regulatory, political, and financial risks. The Board exercises its role of risk oversight in a variety of ways, including the following:
</P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="20%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="77%"></TD></TR>


<TR BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#284993"><B>Board&nbsp;of Directors</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; "><B>&#149;</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">Monitors overall corporate performance, the integrity of financial and other controls, and the effectiveness of the Company&#146;s legal
compliance and enterprise risk management programs, risk governance practices, and risk mitigation efforts, particularly with regard to those risks specified by the Company as &#147;Risk Factors&#148; in its Annual Report on Form 10-K</TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; "><B>&#149;</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">Oversees management&#146;s implementation and utilization of appropriate risk management systems at all levels of the Company, including operating companies, business
units, corporate departments, and service companies</TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; "><B>&#149;</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">Reviews specific facilities and operational risks as part of visits to Company operations</TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; "><B>&#149;</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">Reviews portfolio, capital allocation, and geopolitical risks in the context of the Board&#146;s annual strategy session and the annual business plan and capital budget
review</TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; "><B>&#149;</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">Receives reports from management on and considers risk matters in the context of the Company&#146;s strategic, business, and operational planning and decision
making</TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; "><B>&#149;</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">Receives reports from management on and routinely considers critical risk topics, including: operational, financial,
geopolitical/legislative, strategic, geological, security, commodity trading, skilled personnel, capital project execution, civil unrest, legal, and technology/cybersecurity risk</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#284993"><B>Audit&nbsp;Committee</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; "><B>&#149;</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">Assists the Board in fulfilling its oversight of financial risk exposures and implementation and effectiveness of Chevron&#146;s compliance programs</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; "><B>&#149;</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">Discusses Chevron&#146;s policies with respect to financial risk assessment and financial risk management</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; "><B>&#149;</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">Meets with Chevron&#146;s Chief Compliance Officer and certain members of Chevron&#146;s Compliance Policy Committee to receive information regarding compliance policies
and procedures and internal controls</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; "><B>&#149;</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">Meets with and reviews reports from Chevron&#146;s independent registered public accounting firm and internal auditors</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; "><B>&#149;</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">Reports its discussions to the full Board for
consideration and action when appropriate</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" ROWSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#284993"><B>Board&nbsp;Nominating&nbsp;and Governance&nbsp;Committee</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; "><B>&#149;</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">Assists the Board in fulfilling its oversight of risks that may arise in connection with the Company&#146;s governance structures and processes</TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; "><B>&#149;</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">Conducts an annual evaluation of the Company&#146;s governance practices with the help of the Corporate Governance department</TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; "><B>&#149;</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">Discusses risk management in the context of general governance matters, including, among other topics, Board and management succession planning, delegations of authority
and internal approval processes, stockholder proposals and activism, and Director and officer liability insurance</TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Reports its discussions to the full Board for consideration and action when
appropriate</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" ROWSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#284993"><B>Management Compensation&nbsp;Committee</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; "><B>&#149;</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">Assists the Board in fulfilling its oversight of risks that may arise in connection with Chevron&#146;s compensation programs and
practices</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; "><B>&#149;</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">Reviews the design and goals of Chevron&#146;s compensation programs and practices in the context of possible risks to Chevron&#146;s financial and reputational
well-being</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; "><B>&#149;</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">Reviews Chevron&#146;s strategies and supporting processes for management succession planning, leadership development, executive retention, and diversity</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; "><B>&#149;</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">Reports its discussions to the full Board for
consideration and action when appropriate</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#284993"><B>Public Policy Committee</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; "><B>&#149;</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">Assists the Board in fulfilling its oversight of risks that may arise in connection with the social, political, environmental, human rights, and public policy aspects of
Chevron&#146;s business and the communities in which it operates</TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; "><B>&#149;</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">Discusses risk management in the context of, among other things, legislative and regulatory initiatives, safety and environmental stewardship, community relations,
government and nongovernmental organization relations, and Chevron&#146;s reputation</TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">

<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Reports its discussions to the full Board
for consideration and action when appropriate</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="70%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">

<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#284993">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP ALIGN="right" BGCOLOR="#284993"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#ffffff">&nbsp;&nbsp;CORPORATE&nbsp;GOVERNANCE&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><A NAME="xtoc304635_119"></A><B>Board and Committee Evaluations
</B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:16pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Each year, your Board and its committees perform a rigorous self-evaluation. As required by Chevron&#146;s
Corporate Governance Guidelines, the Board Nominating and Governance Committee oversees this process. The performance evaluations solicit anonymous input from Directors regarding the performance and effectiveness of the Board, the Board committees,
and individual Directors and provide an opportunity for Directors to identify improvements. In addition, the independent Lead Director has individual conversations with each member of the Board,
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
providing further opportunity for dialogue and improvement. The&nbsp;Board Nominating and Governance Committee reviews the results and feedback from the evaluation process and makes
recommendations for improvements as appropriate. The independent Lead Director leads a discussion of the evaluation results during an executive session of the Board and communicates relevant feedback to the CEO. Your Board has successfully used this
process to evaluate Board and committee effectiveness and identify opportunities to strengthen the Board. </P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:24pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B><A NAME="xtoc304635_29"></A>Succession Planning and Leadership Development </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:16pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Succession planning and leadership development are top priorities for your Board and management. Annually,
the non-employee Directors review candidates for all senior management positions to ensure that qualified candidates are available for all positions and that development plans are being utilized to
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
strengthen the skills and qualifications of candidates. To assist the non-employee Directors, the CEO periodically provides them with an assessment of senior executives and their potential to
succeed to the position of CEO, as well as perspectives on potential candidates for other senior management positions. </P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:24pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B><A NAME="xtoc304635_30"></A>Corporate Governance Guidelines </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:16pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Your Board has adopted Corporate Governance Guidelines to provide a transparent framework for the effective governance of Chevron. The Corporate
Governance Guidelines are reviewed regularly and updated as appropriate. The full text of the Corporate Governance Guidelines can be found on our website at <I>www.chevron.com</I>. They address, among other topics: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">the role of the Board </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Board membership criteria </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Director independence </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Board size </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Director terms of office </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">the election of Directors </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

 <P STYLE="font-size:24pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B><A NAME="xtoc304635_31"></A>Business Conduct and Ethics Code </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:16pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">We have adopted a code of business conduct and ethics for Directors, officers (including the Company&#146;s Chief Executive Officer, Chief Financial
Officer, and Comptroller), and employees, known as the Business Conduct and Ethics Code. The code is available on our website at <I>www.chevron.com</I> and is available in print upon request. We will post any amendments to the code on our website.
</P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

 COLOR="#284993"><B></B></FONT></TD>

<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP BGCOLOR="#284993"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#ffffff">&nbsp;&nbsp;CORPORATE&nbsp;GOVERNANCE&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><A NAME="xtoc304635_32"></A><B>Engagement</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:16pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="97%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt" BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8">
<P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Your Board believes that fostering long-term and institution-wide relationships with stockholders and maintaining their trust and goodwill is a core
Chevron objective. Chevron conducts extensive engagements with key stockholders. These engagements routinely cover governance, compensation, social, safety, environmental, human rights, and other current and emerging issues. In addition, we have an
extensive investor relations outreach effort, in which members of senior management routinely meet with major investors to review Company strategies, financial and operating performance, capital allocation priorities, and near-term outlook. We use
all of these sessions to ensure that the Board and management understand and address the issues that are important to our stockholders.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt" BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">In an effort to continuously improve Chevron&#146;s governance processes and communications, Chevron has developed and
follows an Annual Engagement Plan and Process to systematically identify and plan its engagements and to proactively address important issues. The Annual Engagement Plan and Process is supervised by an Engagement Steering Committee, which is
composed of senior executive officers. The
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
Engagement Steering Committee meets periodically to discuss engagement efforts and key issues and trends. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Since Chevron&#146;s last Annual Meeting, an engagement team consisting of senior executives, subject matter experts on governance, compensation, and
environmental and social issues, and, when appropriate, our independent Lead Director and the Chair of our Management Compensation Committee, conducted more than 45 in-depth discussions with stockholders representing more than 36 percent of
Chevron&#146;s outstanding common stock. Of those meetings, our Lead Director and Chairman of our Management Compensation Committee met with stockholders comprising 29 percent of our outstanding stock. In addition, our engagement team met with many
of the stockholders who submitted proposals for inclusion in our Proxy Statement to discuss their concerns and areas of agreement and disagreement. Chevron gained valuable feedback during these engagements, and this feedback was shared with the
Board and its relevant committees. For more information about these engagements, see the &#147;Board Leadership and Independent Lead Director&#148; and &#147;Compensation Discussion and Analysis&#148; sections of the Proxy Statement.
</P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:24pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><A NAME="xtoc304635_33"></A><B>Communicating With the Board</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:16pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The Board Nominating and Governance Committee reviews interested-party communications, including stockholder inquiries directed to non-employee
Directors. The Corporate Secretary and Chief Governance Officer compiles the communications, summarizes lengthy or repetitive communications, and regularly compiles the communications received, the responses sent, and further action, if any. All
communications are available to the Directors. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="86%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="98%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD></TD></TR>


<TR BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Interested
parties wishing to communicate their concerns or questions about Chevron to the independent Lead Director or any other non-employee Directors may do so by mail addressed to the Lead Director or Non-employee Directors, c/o Office of the Corporate
Secretary and Chief Governance Officer, 6001 Bollinger Canyon Road, San Ramon, CA 94583-2324 or by email to <I>corpgov@chevron.com</I>.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:20pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><A NAME="xtoc304635_34"></A><B>Related Person Transactions</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:16pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="justify"><B>Review and Approval of Related Person Transactions </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">It is our policy that all employees and Directors must avoid any activity that is in conflict with, or has the appearance of conflicting with,
Chevron&#146;s business interests. This policy is included in our Business Conduct and Ethics Code. Directors and executive officers must inform the Chairman and the Corporate Secretary and Chief Governance Officer when confronted with any situation
that may be perceived as a conflict of interest. In addition, at least annually, each Director and executive officer completes a detailed questionnaire specifying any business relationship that may give rise to a conflict of interest. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Your Board has charged the Board Nominating and Governance Committee to review related person transactions as defined by U.S. Securities and Exchange
Commission (SEC) rules. The Committee has adopted guidelines to assist it with this review. Under these guidelines, all executive officers, Directors, and Director nominees must promptly advise the Corporate Secretary and Chief Governance Officer of
any proposed or actual business and financial affiliations involving themselves or their immediate family members that, to the best of their knowledge after reasonable inquiry, could reasonably be expected to give rise to a reportable related person
transaction. The Corporate Secretary
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
and Chief Governance Officer will prepare a report summarizing any potentially reportable transactions, and the Committee will review these reports and determine whether to approve or ratify the
identified transaction. The Committee has identified the following categories of transactions that are deemed to be preapproved by the Committee, even if the aggregate amount involved exceeds the $120,000 reporting threshold identified in the SEC
rules: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">compensation paid to an executive officer if that executive officer&#146;s compensation is otherwise reported in our
Proxy Statement or if the executive officer is not an immediate family member of another Chevron executive officer or Director; </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">compensation paid to a Director for service as a Director if that compensation is otherwise reportable in our Proxy
Statement; </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">transactions in which the related person&#146;s interest arises solely as a stockholder and all stockholders receive the
same benefit on a pro-rata basis; </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">transactions involving competitive bids (unless the bid is awarded to a related person who was not the lowest bidder or
unless the bidding process did not involve the use of formal procedures normally associated with our competitive bidding procedures);
</P></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">transactions involving services as a common or contract carrier or public utility in which rates or charges are fixed by
law; </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">transactions involving certain banking-related services under terms comparable with similarly situated transactions;
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">transactions conducted in the ordinary course of business in which our Director&#146;s interest arises solely because he
or she is a director of another entity and the transaction does not exceed $5&nbsp;million or 5 percent (whichever is greater) of the receiving entity&#146;s consolidated gross revenues for that year; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">charitable contributions by Chevron to an entity in which our Director&#146;s interest arises solely because he or she is
a director, trustee, or similar advisor to the entity and the contributions do not exceed, in the aggregate, $1&nbsp;million or 2 percent (whichever is greater) of that entity&#146;s gross revenues for that year; and
</P></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">transactions conducted in the ordinary course of business and our Director&#146;s interest arises solely because he or
she owns an equity or limited partnership interest in the entity and the transaction does not exceed 2 percent of the total equity or partnership interests of the entity. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The Committee reviews all relevant information, including the amount of all business transactions involving Chevron and the entity with which the Director
or executive officer is associated, and determines whether to approve or ratify the transaction. A Director will abstain from decisions regarding transactions involving that Director or his or her family members. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="justify"><B>Related Person Transactions </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">There were no
related person transactions for the period covered by this Proxy Statement. </P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:24pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B><A NAME="xtoc304635_35"></A>Board Nominating and Governance Committee Report </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:16pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The Board Nominating and Governance Committee (the Committee) is responsible for recommending to the Board
the qualifications for Board membership, identifying, assessing, and recommending qualified Director candidates for the Board&#146;s consideration, assisting the Board in organizing itself to discharge its duties and responsibilities, and providing
oversight of Chevron&#146;s corporate governance practices and policies, including an effective process for stockholders to communicate with the Board. The Committee is composed entirely of independent Directors as defined by the NYSE Corporate
Governance Standards and operates under a written charter. The Committee&#146;s charter is available on Chevron&#146;s website at <I>www.chevron.com</I> and is available in print upon request. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The Committee&#146;s role in and process for identifying and evaluating prospective Director nominees, including nominees recommended by stockholders, is
described in the &#147;Election of Directors&#148; section of this Proxy Statement. In addition, the Committee makes recommendations to the Board concerning Director independence, Board committee assignments, committee chairs, Audit Committee
&#147;financial experts,&#148; and the financial literacy of Audit Committee members. The Committee also reviews the process and the results of the annual performance evaluations of the Board, Board committees, and individual Directors. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The Committee regularly reviews trends and recommends best practices, initiates improvements, and plays a leadership role in maintaining Chevron&#146;s
strong corporate governance structures and practices. Among the practices the Committee believes demonstrate the Company&#146;s commitment to strong corporate governance are the following: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">annual election of all Directors; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">supermajority of independent Directors; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">majority vote standard for the election of Directors in uncontested elections, coupled with a Director resignation
policy; </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">annual election of the Chairman of the Board by independent Directors;
</P></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">annual election of an independent Lead Director by independent Directors when the Chief Executive Officer is elected as
Chairman; </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">no supermajority voting provisions in the Restated Certificate of&nbsp;Incorporation or By-Laws. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Stockholders can find additional information concerning Chevron&#146;s corporate governance structures and practices in Chevron&#146;s Corporate
Governance Guidelines, By-Laws, and Restated Certificate of Incorporation, copies of which are available on Chevron&#146;s website at <I>www.chevron.com</I> and are available in print upon request. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><I>Respectfully submitted on March&nbsp;28, 2017, by members of the Board Nominating and Governance Committee of your Board: </I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Ronald D. Sugar, Chair </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Wanda M. Austin </P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Inge G. Thulin </P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP BGCOLOR="#284993"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#ffffff">&nbsp;&nbsp;CORPORATE&nbsp;GOVERNANCE&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD></TR></TABLE> <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B><A NAME="xtoc304635_36"></A>Management Compensation Committee Report </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:16pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The Management Compensation Committee (the Committee) of Chevron has reviewed and discussed with management the Compensation Discussion and Analysis
beginning on page&nbsp;29 of this Proxy Statement. Based on such review and discussion, the Committee recommended to the Board of Directors of the Corporation that the Compensation Discussion and Analysis be included in this Proxy Statement and
incorporated by reference into the Corporation&#146;s Annual Report on Form 10-K. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><I>Respectfully submitted on March&nbsp;28, 2017, by members of the
Management Compensation Committee of your Board: </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:57%; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">Enrique Hernandez, Jr., Chair </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:57%; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">Robert E. Denham </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:57%; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">Ronald D. Sugar </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:57%; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">Inge G. Thulin </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B><A NAME="xtoc304635_37"></A>Audit Committee Report </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:16pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial"><B>Roles and Responsibilities.
</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">The Audit Committee (the Committee) assists your Board in fulfilling its responsibility to provide independent, objective oversight of Chevron&#146;s financial reporting and internal control processes. The
Committee&#146;s charter can be viewed on Chevron&#146;s website at <I>www.chevron.com</I> under the tabs <I>&#147;Investors&#148;</I> and <I>&#147;Corporate Governance.&#148;</I> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Management is responsible for preparing Chevron&#146;s financial statements in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles in the United
States (U.S. GAAP) and for developing, maintaining, and evaluating disclosure controls and procedures and internal control over financial reporting. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The Company&#146;s independent registered public accounting firm&#151;PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP (PwC)&#151;is responsible for expressing an opinion on
the conformity of Chevron&#146;s financial statements with U.S. GAAP and on the effectiveness of Chevron&#146;s internal control over financial reporting. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial"><B>Required Disclosures and Discussions. </B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">In discharging its oversight role, the
Committee reviewed and discussed with management and PwC the audited financial statements for the&nbsp;year ended December&nbsp;31, 2016, as contained in the 2016 Annual Report on Form 10-K, and management&#146;s and PwC&#146;s evaluation of
Chevron&#146;s internal control over financial reporting. The Committee routinely met privately with PwC and discussed
</FONT></P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
issues deemed significant by PwC. The Committee has discussed with PwC the matters required to be discussed by Auditing Standard 1301, &#147;Communications With Audit Committees,&#148; as adopted
by the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (PCAOB). </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">In addition, the Committee discussed with PwC its independence from Chevron and
Chevron&#146;s management; received the written disclosures required by the PCAOB regarding PwC&#146;s independence; and considered whether the provision of nonaudit services was compatible with maintaining PwC&#146;s independence. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial"><B>Committee Recommendation. </B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">In reliance on the reviews and discussions
outlined above, the Committee recommended to your Board that the audited financial statements be included in Chevron&#146;s Annual Report on Form 10-K for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2016, for filing with the U.S. Securities and Exchange
Commission. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><I>Respectfully submitted on February&nbsp;22, 2017, by the members of the Audit Committee of your Board: </I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Charles W. Moorman IV, Chair </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Robert E. Denham </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Jon M. Huntsman Jr. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Dambisa F. Moyo
</P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
