<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-left:8pt; padding-right:2pt"><B>Chevron&#146;s Named Executive Officers, or NEOs</B></TD></TR>


<TR BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-left:8pt; padding-right:2pt"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">John S. Watson,
Chairman and Chief Executive Officer</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-left:8pt; padding-right:2pt"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Patricia E.
Yarrington, Vice President and Chief Financial Officer</P></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-left:8pt; padding-right:2pt"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Michael K. Wirth,
Vice Chairman and Executive Vice President, Midstream and Development</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-left:8pt; padding-right:2pt"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">James W. Johnson,
Executive Vice President, Upstream</P></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-left:8pt; padding-right:2pt">
<P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Joseph C. Geagea, Executive Vice President, Technology, Projects and Services</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Our Pay Philosophy</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Our compensation programs have been designed with several important values and objectives in mind: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Pay competitively across all salary grades and all geographies; our target compensation is determined by benchmarking
comparable positions at other companies of equivalent size, scale, complexity, capital intensity, and geographic footprint. We reference both oil industry peers and non-oil industry peers in this analysis; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Incentivize balanced short- and long-term decision-making in support of a long-cycle-time business with a career-oriented
employment model; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Pay for absolute and competitive performance, in alignment with stockholder returns; and </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Apply compensation program rules in a manner that is internally consistent. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The MCC believes that a majority of an executive&#146;s pay should be composed of awards that are directly tied to Company and individual performance and
considers all elements of pay together when setting awards. </P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Use of Peer Groups</B>
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">We are always competing for the best talent with our direct industry peers and with the broader market. Accordingly, the MCC regularly reviews
the market data, pay practices, and compensation ranges among both industry and nonindustry peers to ensure that we continue to offer a reasonable and competitive executive pay program each year. Our core peer group is reviewed regularly by the MCC
and has had very few changes over the years. Throughout this Compensation Discussion and Analysis, we refer to three distinct peer groups, as described below. We source peer company data from compensation consultant surveys and public disclosures.
</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="20%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="77%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><B>Peer Group</B></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"><B>Description</B></TD></TR>


<TR BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial"><B>Oil Industry Peer Group</B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial"><B></B><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">(13&nbsp;companies)</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial"><B></B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">Companies with substantial U.S. or global operations that
closely approximate the size, scope, and complexity of our business or segments of our business.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">This is the primary peer group used to understand how each NEO&#146;s total compensation compares with the total compensation for reasonably similar industry-specific
positions at these companies.</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial"><B><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Oil</FONT>
<BR>Industry Peer Group</B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial"><B></B><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">(22&nbsp;companies)</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial"><B></B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">Companies that are of significant financial and
operational size and that have, among other features, global operations, significant assets and capital requirements, long-term project investment cycles, extensive technology portfolios, an emphasis on engineering and technical skills, and
extensive distribution channels.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">This is the secondary peer group used to periodically compare
our overall compensation practices (and those of the oil and energy industry, generally) against a broader mix <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">of&nbsp;non-oil</FONT> companies that are similar to Chevron in size, complexity and scope of
operations.</P></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial"><B>LTIP Performance Share Peer Group</B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial"><B></B><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">(4&nbsp;companies and 1 stock index)</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial"><B></B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">Companies used to compare our TSR for the purpose of
determining performance share payout:</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.25em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;For LTIP grants issued prior to 2017: BP, ExxonMobil, Royal Dutch Shell, and Total</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.25em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Effective with 2017 LTIP grant: BP, ExxonMobil, Royal Dutch
Shell, Total, and S&amp;P 500 Total Return Index</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">The inclusion of S&amp;P 500 Total Return Index
broadens the performance benchmark beyond industry peers and requires Chevron to outperform both industry peers and a market-based index in order to receive maximum payout. The MCC believes this further aligns executive pay with long-term
stockholder interests.</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">

Statement</I></FONT><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B></B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#284993">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP ALIGN="right" BGCOLOR="#284993"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#ffffff">&nbsp;&nbsp;EXECUTIVE&nbsp;COMPENSATION&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The Oil Industry Peer Group companies most similar to Chevron in size, complexity, geographic reach,
business lines, and location of operations are BP, ExxonMobil, Royal Dutch Shell, and Total. These companies are key competitors for stockholder investments within the larger global energy sector. We also compete for stockholder investment and
employee talent with smaller U.S. companies, including the larger independent exploration and production companies and the larger independent refining and marketing companies.
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Oil</FONT> Industry Peer Group includes capital-intensive, global,
large-scale, and high-complexity company comparators. The median market cap (as of 12/31/2016) of the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Oil</FONT> Industry Peer Group was $92&nbsp;billion (vs. $222&nbsp;billion for Chevron) and the median sales
for 2016 were $48&nbsp;billion (vs. $103&nbsp;billion for Chevron). </P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="50%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="49%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g304635g57g50.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g304635g43o21.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Components of Executive Compensation</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The material components of our executive compensation program and their purposes and key characteristics
are as follows: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Base salary </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Annual incentive plan (Chevron Incentive Plan)
</P></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Long-Term Incentive Plan, including performance shares, stock options and restricted stock units </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Benefits, including retirement plans, savings plans and other perquisites
</P></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Base Salary</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Base salary is a fixed, competitive component of pay based on responsibilities, skills and experience. Base salaries are reviewed periodically in light of
market practices and changes in responsibilities. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>How Base Salaries Are Determined </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Base salaries are determined through market surveys of positions of comparable level, scope, complexity,
and responsibility. There is no <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-determined</FONT> target or range within the Oil Industry Peer Group or the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Oil</FONT> Industry Peer Group as an objective for
Mr.&nbsp;Watson&#146;s base salary. Instead, the MCC takes into account the data provided by the MCC&#146;s independent consultant, the relative size, scope, and complexity of our business, Mr.&nbsp;Watson&#146;s performance and the aggregate amount
of Mr.&nbsp;Watson&#146;s compensation package. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">For the other NEOs, each executive officer is assigned a base salary grade. The MCC annually reviews
the base salary grade
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
ranges and may approve changes in the ranges based on business conditions and comparative peer group data (primarily the Oil Industry Peer Group) provided by the MCC&#146;s independent
consultant. Within each salary grade range, the MCC makes base salary determinations for each NEO taking into account individual qualitative considerations, such as individual performance, experience, skills, competitive positioning, retention
objectives, and leadership responsibilities. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The independent Directors of the Board approve the compensation of the CEO and ratify the compensation
of the other NEOs. </P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="96%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B><SUB STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:bottom"></SUB></B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993"><I>Chevron Corporation&#151;2017 Proxy Statement</I></FONT><FONT
 COLOR="#284993"><B></B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">35</TD></TR></TABLE>

<TD VALIGN="top"></TD></TR></TABLE> <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Adjustments in 2016 Base Salaries
</B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">After taking into account the market conditions and survey data, the MCC made no changes to any of the NEO
salary grade ranges for 2016 compensation. As to individual salary changes, the MCC
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
held the CEO&#146;s base salary flat and adjusted our other NEOs&#146; base salaries in 2016 reflective of their 2015 performance, experience and competitive benchmarks.

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Adjustments in 2017 Base Salaries </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">After taking into account the market condition and survey data, the MCC made no changes to any of the NEO
salary grade ranges for 2017 compensation. As to individual salary changes, the MCC held CEO base salary flat and adjusted our other NEOs&#146; base salaries in 2017 (ranging from 3.8&nbsp;percent to 13.8 percent) reflective of their 2016
performance, experience, and competitive
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
benchmarks. Mike Wirth received a 13.8&nbsp;percent increase in base salary due to his increased responsibility as a result of his promotion in 2017. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">See page 47 in the Compensation Tables for base salary changes over time.
</P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Annual Incentive Plan
(Chevron Incentive Plan) </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The Chevron Incentive Plan is designed to recognize annual performance achievements based on the MCC&#146;s
assessment of Company performance across four broad categories: financial, capital management, operating performance, and health, environment and safety. Each category contains multiple performance measures, reflecting outcomes on both short-term
and long-term measures on absolute, relative, and time-series performance. The CIP also recognizes individual leadership
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
through measurable individual contributions. The award is delivered as an annual cash bonus based on a percentage of base salary and makes up approximately 11 percent of the CEO&#146;s annual
compensation and on average 14&nbsp;percent of all other NEOs&#146; annual compensation. The CIP award determination process is consistent across more than 50,000 <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">CIP-eligible</FONT> Chevron employees, with the award
target varying by pay grade. </P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The CIP award for the CEO and the
other NEOs is calculated as follows: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="12%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="17%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="32%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="27%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER:1.00pt solid #284993; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><B>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Base&nbsp;Salary&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="right"><B><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt">x</FONT>&nbsp;</B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #284993; BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #284993; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #284993">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #284993; BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #284993; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #284993">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="center"><B>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Award&nbsp;Target&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="center"><B><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt">x</FONT>&nbsp;</B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #284993; BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #284993; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #284993">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #284993; BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #284993; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #284993"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="center"><B>Corporate
Performance Rating</B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="center"><B><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt">x</FONT>&nbsp;</B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #284993; BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #284993; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #284993">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #284993; BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #284993; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #284993; padding-right:2pt">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="center"><B>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Individual&nbsp;Performance&nbsp;Factor&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center"><B><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:18pt" COLOR="#284993"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:'WINGDINGS 3'">&#192;</FONT></FONT></B></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center"><B><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:18pt" COLOR="#284993"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:'WINGDINGS 3'">&#192;</FONT></FONT></B></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center"><B><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:18pt" COLOR="#284993"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:'WINGDINGS 3'">&#192;</FONT></FONT></B></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.38em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">Before the beginning of each
performance year, the MCC establishes a CIP Award Target for the CEO and the other NEOs, which is based on a percentage of the NEO&#146;s base salary.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:0.38em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">The MCC sets award target with reference to the median award of our Oil Industry Peer Group. All individuals in the same salary grade have the same
target, which provides internal equity and consistency.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.38em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">After the end of the
performance year, the MCC systematically reviews and assesses Company performance metrics, and sets the Corporate Performance Rating based on a range of measures in four categories.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.38em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">Performance is viewed across multiple parameters (absolute results; results vs.
plan; results vs. Oil Industry Peer Group and/or general industry; performance trends over time). The performance metrics are also assessed taking into account the elements that may be market driven or otherwise beyond the control of management. See
pages 38-39 for a discussion of 2016 performance.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:0.38em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">The minimum Corporate
Performance Rating is zero (i.e., no award), and the maximum is two (i.e., 200&nbsp;percent of target).</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.38em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">The MCC
also takes into account individual performance. This is largely a personal leadership dimension, recognizing the individual&#146;s effort, initiative and impact.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.38em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The CEO recommends to the MCC an Individual Performance Factor (IPF) for each NEO other than himself.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:0.38em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">The MCC determines the final IPF for the CEO and the other NEOs. The
independent directors of the Board approve the IPF for the CEO and ratify the IPF for the other NEOs.</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="96%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="right"><B>36</B></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B><SUB STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:bottom"></SUB></B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993"><I>Chevron Corporation&#151;2017 Proxy
Statement</I></FONT><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B></B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV ALIGN="right">
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="70%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="26%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="25%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#284993">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP ALIGN="right" BGCOLOR="#284993"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#ffffff">&nbsp;&nbsp;EXECUTIVE&nbsp;COMPENSATION&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Chevron goes through a rigorous goal-setting and performance review process to determine the CIP Corporate
Performance Rating. Annually, Business Plan targets are determined after thorough reviews and approvals by the Strategy and Planning Committee (S&amp;PC), a subcommittee of the Executive Committee, and the Board. The S&amp;PC is responsible for
setting targets that challenge the Company to optimize strategies and portfolio composition and to improve operational performance to create
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
stockholder value. Robust annual performance measures, weightings, and goals are established alongside the Business Plan subject to review and approval by the MCC.
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Mid-year</FONT> and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">end-of-year</FONT></FONT> reviews by the Board and the MCC systematically assess progress against these measures. The MCC has the
discretion to adjust the CIP award downward if it determines that business or economic considerations warrant such an adjustment.
</P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Changes to the CIP </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">In response to extensive stockholder engagements, the MCC approved the following changes to our CIP program beginning with the 2016 performance year: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">CIP awards are capped at 200&nbsp;percent of target. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">The corporate performance components and weightings have been revised to place more emphasis on project performance and
capital management. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="10">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="10" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">We established &#147;capital management&#148; as its own category with 30&nbsp;percent weighting. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="10">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="10" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">We expanded the ROCE metrics to include annual and rolling five-year performance against peers. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="10">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="10" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">We identified specific, targeted project development objectives to measure progress on key capital investment programs.
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Our CIP disclosure on pages&nbsp;38 to 39 provides additional details to explain the performance results and the corporate
performance rating. </P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>2016 CIP Corporate Performance Rating </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">In January 2017, the MCC evaluated Chevron&#146;s 2016 performance across the four categories&#151;financial, capital management, operating performance,
and health, environment and safety&#151;and assigned an overall CIP corporate performance rating of 0.75. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">In order to determine the 2016 Corporate
Performance Rating, a raw score range was assigned based on the Company&#146;s actual performance with respect to the particular performance measures comprising each category as measured against the Company&#146;s Business Plan objectives. This raw
score can span from zero (reflecting very poor performance) to two (reflecting outstanding performance) for each category. Category weights are then applied to the raw score ranges to determine an overall range. When determining the Corporate
Performance Rating, the MCC may apply discretion when assessing the Company&#146;s absolute performance against the Business Plan objectives and the Company&#146;s performance relative to competitors.
</P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="96%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B><SUB STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:bottom"></SUB></B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993"><I>Chevron Corporation&#151;2017 Proxy Statement</I></FONT><FONT
 COLOR="#284993"><B></B></FONT></TD>

efforts to lower costs mostly offset impairment charges, which were in part triggered by the low price environment. On an absolute basis, Chevron reported a loss of $0.5&nbsp;billion and a loss
of $0.27 per share, reflecting low commodity prices. </P></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#284993">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP ALIGN="right" BGCOLOR="#284993"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#ffffff">&nbsp;&nbsp;EXECUTIVE&nbsp;COMPENSATION&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt"><I>Net cash flow</I>&#151;We remain on target to be cash flow breakeven at $50 Brent in 2017. Absent the impact of
commodity prices, 2016 net cash flow was better than the Business Plan because of actions taken to lower operating expenses, restructure staff, and curtail capital investments. On an absolute basis, net cash flow was $(11.8) billion, reflecting low
commodity prices. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt"><I>Divestiture proceeds</I>&#151;$2.8&nbsp;billion in sales proceeds were realized in 2016. Although less than the
original Business Plan, several transactions progressed in 2016 that are expected to close within the first half of 2017, and we expect to attain the upper end of the targeted $5&nbsp;billion to $10&nbsp;billion in asset sale proceeds over the
2016&#150;2017 timeframe. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Based on the preceding, the raw score range assigned to this category for the 2016 performance year was 0.60&#150;0.70
out of a maximum of 2.0. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Capital Management&#151;30 Percent </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt"><I>Return on capital employed</I> <I>(ROCE)</I>&#151;2016 annual ROCE performance beat the Business Plan objective,
excluding commodity price impacts. Reported ROCE for 2016 was (0.1) percent, reflecting very weak commodity prices. The Company&#146;s relative five-year ROCE performance vs. peers deteriorated slightly, reflecting Chevron&#146;s
Upstream&#150;weighted and, within Upstream, <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">oil-weighted</FONT> (vs. natural gas&#150;weighted) portfolio. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt"><I>Capital and exploratory expenditures (C&amp;E)</I>&#151;C&amp;E totaled $22.4&nbsp;billion in 2016, $4.2&nbsp;billion
or 16&nbsp;percent lower than the Business Plan. Deliberate pacing, prioritizing and high-grading of investments in response to the weak commodity price environment occurred. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Major milestones: </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="10">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="10" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Gorgon&#151;First cargo for Gorgon Train 1 loaded in first quarter per the Business Plan. Some production interruptions
occurred in subsequent months. Gorgon Train 2 loaded its first cargo in fourth quarter per the Business Plan and has delivered a quick <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">ramp-up</FONT> and steady, high plant utilization since then. Gorgon Train 3 was
on track for first production in mid 2017, per Business Plan, and started up ahead of schedule in first quarter 2017. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="10">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="10" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Wheatstone&#151;On track to deliver first production in <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">mid-2017</FONT> per the Business
Plan. Some slippage in platform commissioning occurred. Total project cost increased to $34&nbsp;billion. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="10">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="10" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Angola LNG&#151;Substantial repair program completed, though some delays were encountered. Stable plant performance
achieved in the fourth quarter. </P></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="10">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="10" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Other projects&#151;Chuandongbei (China), Alder (U.K. North Sea) and Bangka (Indonesia) projects were started on time.
Mafumeira Sul (Angola) startup was delayed by one quarter, into the first quarter of 2017. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Based on the preceding, the raw score range assigned to this category for the 2016 performance year was 0.60&#150;0.70
out of a maximum of 2.0. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Operating Performance&#151;15 Percent </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Net production of 2.594&nbsp;million barrels of <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">oil-equivalent</FONT> per day was
slightly below the external guidance provided at the beginning of the year, for which management is held accountable. A large shortfall occurred in the Partitioned Zone, where production was not <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">re-started</FONT>
midyear, as originally anticipated. There were some delays in the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">ramp-ups</FONT> and timing of certain major capital projects, but these impacts were largely offset by higher production from our U.S. shale and tight
assets, where production exceeded the Business Plan. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Operating expenses and selling, general and administrative expenses totaled $25.0&nbsp;billion, well under the Business
Plan and $2.5&nbsp;billion lower than 2015. Over the past two years, our costs have declined 16&nbsp;percent. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Refining unit utilization rates exceeded the Business Plan by 1.4&nbsp;percent. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Based on the preceding, the raw score range assigned to this category for the 2016 performance year was 0.90&#150;1.00
out of a maximum of 2.0. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Health, Environment and Safety&#151;15 Percent </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Maintained industry-leading personal safety rates, better than the Business Plan and achieving record lows on most
measures, including the Days Away From Work Rate and Total Recordable Incidents Rate. The opportunity for improvements is still evident in lowering the incidence of high-consequence, <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">low-probability</FONT> events.
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Achieved record low spills and had continued improvement in lowering both the number and the impact of loss of
containment incidents. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Based on the preceding, the raw score range assigned to this category for the 2016 performance year was 0.80&#150;0.90
out of a maximum of 2.0. </P></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>2016 NEO CIP Awards
</B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The MCC and the independent Directors of the Board assessed corporate and individual performance in making
CIP awards based on 2016 performance. The MCC would normally consider individual adjustments for the CEO and the other NEOs based on review of the individual&#146;s impact on the financial and operational success during the year. However, given the
significant transformation that took place in all of Chevron&#146;s business segments in 2016 and many Company achievements in a
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
challenging year, the MCC chose to recognize the collective effort and treat the executive leadership as one team. Therefore, the CEO and the other NEOs all received a 1.0 Individual Performance
Factor (IPF) and their bonuses were equally impacted by the overall 2016 company performance. This does not represent a change in overall compensation philosophy. The MCC desires and will continue to evaluate individual performance and make
appropriate differentiation in compensation decisions in future years. </P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B><SUB STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:bottom"></SUB></B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993"><I>Chevron Corporation&#151;2017 Proxy Statement</I></FONT><FONT

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="70%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="25%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="26%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP BGCOLOR="#284993"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#ffffff">&nbsp;&nbsp;EXECUTIVE&nbsp;COMPENSATION&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD></TR></TABLE> <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Long-Term Incentive Plan
</B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The key objective of our Long-Term Incentive Plan is to encourage performance that drives stockholder value
over the long-term. The target value of an NEO&#146;s LTIP award at grant time is determined by the MCC, with input from its independent compensation consultant and referencing external benchmark comparisons. The objective is to ensure that Chevron
is competitive against its industry peer companies on the overall target compensation (cash plus equity), after allowing for appropriate differentiation based on size, scale, scope, and job responsibilities. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Each year in January, the MCC determines a target value of LTIP awards for the CEO and the other NEOs based on industry competitive data. These awards
provide incentive compensation opportunities tied to Chevron&#146;s future long-term performance.
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">In setting the LTIP target value for the CEO, the MCC relies on input from its independent compensation
consultant and benchmark research, focusing on the form and amount of similar compensation opportunities in the Oil Industry Peer Group. The MCC also considers the CEO&#146;s demonstrated performance and the Company&#146;s size, scope, and
complexity relative to the comparison companies. Similarly, for the other NEOs, the MCC sets an annual LTIP target value for each salary grade as a multiple of salary, referencing median incentive opportunities for executives in similar positions at
companies in the Oil Industry Peer Group. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The LTIP award represents a pay opportunity. The ultimate realized value of equity-based awards is
determined by absolute and relative stock price performance over a three- to <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10-year</FONT> period.
</P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Changes to LTIP Components
</B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Based on recent input from stockholders, Chevron adopted three changes for the 2017 LTIP program, described
below and further in the table: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Restricted stock units (RSUs) are now a routine component of equity awards, and the proportion of performance shares,
stock options and restricted stock units has changed; </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">The S&amp;P 500 Total Return Index will be added as a fifth competitor in determining performance share awards. The
inclusion of the S&amp;P 500 Total Return Index broadens the peer
</P></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="10">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
group and imposes a stringent market-based performance hurdle for payout. It reflects the fact that stockholders have a wide range of investment choices, inside and outside the energy industry;
and </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Performance shares and RSUs now accrue dividend equivalents that are reinvested as additional shares and/or units and are
paid at the end of the vesting period. The inclusion of dividends aligns better with Chevron&#146;s stockholder value strategy and is a common practice among oil industry and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-oil</FONT> industry peers.
</P></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="18%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>

<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="38%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>

<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>

<TD></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><B>Component</B></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><B>2016</B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><B>Proportion</B></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><B>2017</B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><B>Proportion</B></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" COLSPAN="30" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000"><B>How It Works</B></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">&nbsp;</TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">Performance Shares</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top">40%</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top">50%</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" COLSPAN="30"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.25em; text-indent:-0.88em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Payout is dependent on
Chevron&#146;s TSR over a three-year period, compared with our LTIP Performance Share Peer Group. Peer group includes S&amp;P 500 Total Return Index for 2017 and forward.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.25em; text-indent:-0.88em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt"></P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#ffffff">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#ffffff"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000" BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><B>Relative TSR ranking</B></P></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" COLSPAN="30" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt"></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.25em; text-indent:-0.88em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Performance shares accrue dividend equivalents that are
reinvested as additional shares, to be paid at the end of the performance period, and subject to the performance modifier.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.25em; text-indent:-0.88em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;MCC can exercise negative discretion to reduce payout.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.25em; text-indent:-0.88em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Actual number of shares granted is determined by dividing the
proportionate value of the NEO&#146;s LTIP award by Chevron&#146;s closing common stock price on the grant date<I>. </I></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.25em; text-indent:-0.88em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Payment is made in cash. Refer to page 52 footnote 2 for
calculation details.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt"></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.25em; text-indent:-0.88em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt"></P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.25em; text-indent:-0.88em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><I></I>&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt"></P>

Options</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">60%</TD>
