<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">25%</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" COLSPAN="30" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.25em; text-indent:-0.88em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Strike price is equal to the closing common stock price on the
grant date.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.25em; text-indent:-0.88em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Options vest and become exercisable <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">one-third</FONT> per year, based on continued service for the first three years, and expire 10 years after the grant date.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.25em; text-indent:-0.88em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Gain realized depends on the common stock price at the
exercise date compared with the strike price.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.25em; text-indent:-0.88em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Actual number of stock options granted is determined by dividing the proportionate value of the NEO&#146;s LTIP award by the Black-Scholes option value on the grant date in accordance with
Grant Date Fair Value calculation as defined by the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC).</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt"></P>

proportionate value of the NEO&#146;s LTIP award by Chevron&#146;s closing common stock price on the grant date.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.25em; text-indent:-0.88em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Five-year cliff vesting lengthens equity holding time.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.25em; text-indent:-0.88em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;RSUs accrue dividend equivalents that are reinvested as
additional units, to be paid at the time of vesting.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.25em; text-indent:-0.88em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;Payment is made in cash based on closing common stock price on the vesting date.</P></TD>

<TD WIDTH="25%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#284993">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP ALIGN="right" BGCOLOR="#284993"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#ffffff">&nbsp;&nbsp;EXECUTIVE&nbsp;COMPENSATION&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><I>Supplemental RSUs</I>: Prior to 2017, RSUs were not a component of the annual equity award mix, but from
time to time the Board approved selective RSU grants to recognize exceptional individual performance that had a direct impact on Chevron&#146;s results and to serve as an additional retention tool for such individuals. Historically, these RSUs
vested at the end of three
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
years. Beginning in 2017, we committed to limited use of supplemental RSU grants for executive officers, except in extraordinary circumstances. Supplemental RSUs, if awarded, will accrue dividend
equivalents that are reinvested as additional units and paid at the end of three years. </P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>LTIP Metrics
</B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The MCC continues to believe that TSR is the best overall <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pay-for-performance</FONT></FONT> measure to align our CEO and other NEOs&#146; performance with stockholder interests. TSR is the standard metric for stockholders to use in measuring the Company&#146;s performance because
it easily allows for meaningful comparisons of our performance relative to other companies within our same industry, and it also allows for easy comparison with our stockholders&#146; other investment alternatives. It is objectively determined by
third-party market participants independent of
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
the Company&#146;s judgment. The MCC believes that Company performance on other measures&#151;operational and financial, over the short-term and long-term&#151;is ultimately reflected in TSR
results. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The majority of the LTIP award derives value directly from TSR (relative and absolute). For the CEO and the other NEOs to earn the
originally targeted compensation, Chevron must show sustained competitive performance and Chevron&#146;s stockholders must be rewarded with competitive TSR results.
</P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>A Closer Look at the LTIP
Mix: Why a Mix of Options, Performance Shares and RSUs? </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The MCC believes the new LTIP mix (50&nbsp;percent performance shares, 25&nbsp;percent stock options and
25&nbsp;percent restricted stock units) offers an improved combination of incentive opportunities. It aligns better with our business objectives and is consistent with prevailing standards. Each vehicle has its own risk-reward profile and a
different time horizon (three-year performance period for performance shares, five-year cliff vesting for restricted stock units and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10-year</FONT> term of stock options). Together, these vehicles align our
executives with stockholder interests over the long-term and reward them for absolute and competitive stock performance.
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="justify">


<IMG SRC="g304635g68s37.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>2014&#150;2016 Performance Share Payout </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The three-year performance period for performance shares granted in January 2014 ended on December&nbsp;31, 2016. For this three-year period, Chevron
ranked No.&nbsp;1 in TSR among the five companies in the LTIP Performance Share Peer Group. This resulted in a payout modifier of 200&nbsp;percent. Refer to &#147;Option Exercises and Stock Vested in Fiscal Year 2016&#148; on pages 52 and 53 for
details on the performance payout calculation. </P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">


<IMG SRC="g304635g53i29.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="16" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(1)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial"><I>Per program rules, based on average stock price for the 20-trading days prior and up
to the listed dates.</I></FONT> </P></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">*</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt">Number of awarded stock options, performance shares, and RSUs was determined based on the Company&#146;s common stock
price on January&nbsp;27, 2016, the grant date Black-Scholes value for stock options, and a performance share factor of 100&nbsp;percent reflecting expected performance at target. As these inputs may vary from those used for financial reporting, the
target value shown above may not match the values presented in the &#147;Summary Compensation Table&#148; or the &#147;Grants of Plan-Based Awards in Fiscal Year 2016&#148; table in this Proxy Statement on pages&nbsp;47 and 49, respectively.
</P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">During 2016 and in prior years, the Board has occasionally approved the grant of RSUs in recognition of
exceptional individual performance. Mr.&nbsp;Wirth received an RSU grant in January 2016, in recognition of outstanding performance and
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
achievements while leading our Downstream business to its best year ever ($7.6&nbsp;billion in earnings in 2015). Starting in 2017, we committed to limited use of supplemental RSU grants except
for extraordinary circumstances. </P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>2017 LTIP Grants
</B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">In January 2017, the MCC approved the following LTIP awards to the CEO and other NEOs. The composition of
the equity awards has changed, as described on pages 40&#150;41. The new compensation program is reflective of recent stockholder input.
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
The Board feels that the new program represents an improved combination of incentive opportunities, is aligned with our business objectives and is consistent with prevailing standards.
</P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Although the composition of the equity
awards has changed, the target value has remained flat for both the CEO and the other NEOs with the exception of Mike Wirth, who received a supplemental RSU grant in 2016. None of the NEOs received a 2017 supplemental RSU grant. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><B>NEO</B></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" COLSPAN="2" NOWRAP ALIGN="right" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="right"><B>2017</B></P>

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">*</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt">Number of awarded stock options, performance shares and RSUs was determined based on the Company&#146;s common stock
price on January&nbsp;25, 2017, the grant date Black-Scholes value for stock options, and a performance share factor of 100&nbsp;percent reflecting expected performance at target. As these inputs may vary from those used for financial reporting, the
target value shown above may not match the values to be presented in the 2018 Proxy Statement&#146;s &#147;Summary Compensation Table&#148; or the &#147;Grants of Plan-Based Awards in Fiscal Year 2017&#148; table. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Why Option Quantities Differ Between Years </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The MCC has granted the same level of LTIP target value to the CEO for the last three years&#151;2015,
2016, and 2017. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Chevron determines the number of options by dividing the proportionate value of the NEO&#146;s LTIP award by the Black-Scholes option
value on the grant date. The methodology is
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
consistent with Grant Date Fair Value as defined by the SEC and as reported in the &#147;Summary Compensation Table.&#148; Black-Scholes values are influenced by stock price at grant date. Lower
Black-Scholes values lead to a higher number of shares being granted. Conversely, higher Black-Scholes values lead to a lower number of shares being granted.
</P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The table below shows options awarded
to the CEO over the past three years. As part of compensation program revisions adopted by Chevron, options compose a smaller percentage of the overall equity award in 2017. This too contributed to the large reduction in options being granted
between 2016 and 2017. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" ALIGN="center">

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV ALIGN="right">
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="70%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">

<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#284993">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP ALIGN="right" BGCOLOR="#284993"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#ffffff">&nbsp;&nbsp;EXECUTIVE&nbsp;COMPENSATION&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Retirement Programs and Other Benefits </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">NEOs, like all other employees, have retirement programs and other benefits as part of their overall compensation package at Chevron. We believe that
these programs and benefits: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Support our long-term investment cycle; and </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Encourage retention and long-term employment. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Retirement Programs </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">All of our
employees, including our NEOs, have access to retirement programs that are designed to enable them to accumulate retirement income. The defined benefit (pension) and defined contribution (401(k)&nbsp;savings)&nbsp;plans allow highly compensated
employees to receive the same benefits they would have earned without the IRS limitations on qualified retirement plans under the Employee Retirement Income and Security Act. The deferred compensation plan allows eligible employees to defer salary,
CIP awards, and LTIP payouts. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="16%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="4%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="27%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="44%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><B>Plan Name</B></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000"><B>Plan Type</B></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000"><B>How It Works</B></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"><B>What&#146;s Disclosed</B></TD></TR>


<TR BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">Chevron Retirement<BR>Plan (CRP)</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">Qualified<BR>Defined<BR>Benefit<BR>(IRS&nbsp;&#167;401(a))</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">Participants are eligible for a pension benefit when they leave the Company as long as they meet age, service, and other provisions under the plan.</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">In the &#147;Summary Compensation Table&#148; and the &#147;Pension Benefits Table&#148; in this Proxy Statement, we report the change in
pension value in 2016 and the present value of each NEO&#146;s accumulated benefit under the CRP. The increase in pension value is not a current cash payment. It represents the increase in the value of the NEOs&#146; pensions, which are paid only
after retirement.</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">Chevron Retirement<BR>Restoration Plan<BR>(RRP)</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">Nonqualified<BR>Defined<BR>Benefit</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">Provides participants with<BR>retirement income that cannot<BR>be&nbsp;paid from the CRP due to</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">IRS limits on compensation</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">and
benefits.<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">1</SUP></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">In the &#147;Pension Benefits Table&#148; and accompanying narrative in this Proxy Statement, we describe how the RRP works and present
the current value of each NEO&#146;s accumulated benefit under the RRP.</TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">Employee Savings<BR>Investment Plan<BR>(ESIP)</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">Qualified<BR>Defined<BR>Contribution<BR>(IRS&nbsp;&#167;401(k))</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">Participants who contribute a percentage of their annual compensation (i.e., base salary and CIP award) are eligible for a Company matching contribution, up to annual IRS limits.<SUP
STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">2</SUP></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">In the footnotes to the &#147;Summary Compensation Table&#148; in this Proxy Statement, we describe Chevron&#146;s contributions to each
NEO&#146;s ESIP account.</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">Employee Savings<BR>Investment Plan&#150;<BR>Restoration Plan<BR>(ESIP&#150;RP)</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">Nonqualified<BR>Defined<BR>Contribution</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">Provides participants with an<BR>additional Company matching<BR>contribution that cannot be paid<BR>into the ESIP due to IRS limits on<BR>compensation and benefits.<SUP
STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">3</SUP></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">In the footnotes to the &#147;Nonqualified Deferred Compensation Table&#148; in this Proxy Statement, we describe how the <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">ESIP-RP</FONT> works. In the &#147;Summary Compensation Table&#148; and the &#147;Nonqualified Deferred Compensation Table,&#148; we present Chevron&#146;s contributions to each NEO&#146;s
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">ESIP-RP</FONT> account.</TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">Deferred<BR>Compensation Plan<BR>(DCP)</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000">Nonqualified<BR>Defined<BR>Contribution</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">Participants can defer up to:</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-0.75em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;90&nbsp;percent of CIP awards and LTIP performance share payouts;
and</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-0.75em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;40&nbsp;percent of base salary above the IRS limit (IRS
&#167;401(a)(17)) for payment after retirement or separation from service.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">In the &#147;Nonqualified Deferred Compensation Table&#148; in this Proxy Statement, we report the aggregate NEO deferrals and earnings
in 2016.</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(1)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt">Employees whose compensation exceeds the limits established by the IRS for covered compensation and benefit levels. IRS
annual compensation limit was $265,000 in 2016. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(2)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt">Participants who contribute at least 2&nbsp;percent of their annual compensation to the ESIP receive a Company matching
contribution of 8&nbsp;percent (or 4&nbsp;percent if they contribute 1 percent). The annual limit for both employer and employee contributions to a qualified defined contribution plan was $53,000 in 2016. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(3)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt">Participants who contribute at least 2&nbsp;percent of their annual compensation to the Deferred Compensation Plan
receive a Company matching contribution of 8&nbsp;percent of their base salary that exceeds the IRS annual compensation limit. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT
 COLOR="#284993"><B>Benefit Programs </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The same health and welfare programs, including post-retirement health care, that are broadly
available to employees on our U.S.&nbsp;payroll also apply to NEOs, with no other special programs except executive physicals (as described below under Perquisites). </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Perquisites </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Perquisites for NEOs
are limited and consist principally of financial counseling fees, executive physicals, home security, and the aggregate incremental costs to Chevron for personal use of Chevron automobiles and aircraft. The MCC periodically reviews our policies with
respect to perquisites. In the &#147;Summary Compensation Table&#148; in this Proxy Statement, we report the value of each NEO&#146;s perquisites for 2016. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

Governance</B> </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:16pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">To ensure independent oversight, stockholder alignment and long-term sustainability, our executive compensation program has
the following governance elements in place. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #284993"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:16pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><FONT

STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993">Stock ownership guidelines</FONT></B></FONT> for the Chief Executive Officer, five times base salary increasing to six times effective 2017; for the Executive Vice Presidents and Chief Financial Officer,
four times base salary</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #284993">&nbsp;</TD>

STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>No excessive perquisites;</B></FONT> all have a specific business rationale</P></TD></TR>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #284993">&nbsp;</TD>

STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993">No individual supplemental executive retirement plans</FONT></B></P></TD></TR>

<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #284993"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:16pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><FONT

<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #284993">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #284993"> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>Clawback provisions</B></FONT> are included in the CIP, LTIP, Deferred Compensation Plan, Retirement Restoration Plan and Employee Savings Investment Plan-Restoration Plan for misconduct</P></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #284993">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #284993"> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial"><B><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993">No stock option repricing, reloads or exchanges without stockholder approval</FONT></B></P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="13"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="13" COLSPAN="2"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="13" COLSPAN="2"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="13" COLSPAN="2"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="13" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #284993"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:16pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" COLOR="#284993">&#10003;</FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #284993">&nbsp;</TD>

<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV ALIGN="right">
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="70%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="26%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>

<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="25%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#284993">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP ALIGN="right" BGCOLOR="#284993"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#ffffff">&nbsp;&nbsp;EXECUTIVE&nbsp;COMPENSATION&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Compensation Governance: Oversight and Administration of the Executive
Compensation Program </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:16pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Role of the Board of Directors&#146; Management Compensation Committee</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The Board of Directors&#146; Management Compensation Committee oversees the executive compensation program.
The MCC works closely with its independent compensation consultant, Meridian Compensation Partners, LLC. and management to review pay and performance relative to the Business Plan approved by the Board and to industry peers. The MCC solicits input
from the CEO concerning the performance and compensation of other NEOs.
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
The CEO does not participate in discussion about his own pay; and proposed change to the compensation of the CEO is recommended by the MCC and approved by the independent Directors of the Board.
A complete description of the MCC&#146;s authority and responsibility is provided in its charter, which is available on our website at <I>www.chevron.com</I> and in print upon request.
</P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Independent Compensation
Advice</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The MCC retains an independent compensation consultant&#151;Meridian Compensation Partners LLC&#151;to
assist with its duties. The MCC first engaged Meridian in <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">mid-2014,</FONT> following a comprehensive <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">request-for-proposal</FONT></FONT> process and
subsequent screening and selection. The MCC has the exclusive right to select, retain and terminate Meridian, as well as to approve any fees, terms and other conditions of its service. Meridian and its lead consultant report directly to the MCC,
but, when directed to do so by the MCC, they work cooperatively with Chevron&#146;s management to develop analyses and proposals for the MCC. Meridian provides the following services to the MCC: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Education on executive compensation trends within and across industries;
</P></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Recommendation regarding compensation philosophy and compensation levels; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Selection of compensation comparator groups; and </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Identification and resolution of technical issues associated with executive compensation plans, including tax,
accounting, and securities regulations. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Meridian does not provide any services to the Company. The MCC is not aware of any work
performed by Meridian that raised any conflicts of interest. </P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Compensation Risk
Management</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The MCC annually undertakes a risk assessment of Chevron&#146;s compensation programs to ensure these
programs are appropriately designed and do not motivate individuals or groups to take risks that are reasonably likely to have a material adverse effect on the Company. Following its most recent comprehensive
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
review of the design, administration and controls of these programs, the MCC was satisfied that Chevron&#146;s programs are well structured with strong governance and oversight mechanisms in
place to minimize and mitigate potential risks. </P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Stock Ownership
Guidelines</B> </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">We require our NEOs to hold prescribed levels of Chevron common stock, further linking their interests with those of our
stockholders. Executives have five years to attain their stock ownership guideline. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">As shown in the table below, for fiscal year 2017, we have
strengthened our CEO stock ownership guidelines from five times base salary to six times base salary. Further, beginning in fiscal year 2017, NEOs who have not attained their stock ownership guidelines will be required to hold shares acquired under
the LTIP program until such ownership requirements are met. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" ALIGN="center">

salary</P></TD></TR>

Officer</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Four times base salary</P></TD>

Executive Officers</P></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">
<P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Two times base salary</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Based upon our <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">250-day</FONT> trailing average stock price ending December&nbsp;31, 2016
($99.96), our CEO had a stock ownership base salary multiple of 8.9, and all other NEOs had an average stock ownership base salary multiple of 4.8. The MCC believes these ownership levels provide adequate focus on our long-term business model. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Employment, Severance and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Change-in-Control</FONT></FONT> Agreements</B>
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">In general, we do not maintain employment, severance, or
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">change-in-control</FONT></FONT> agreements with our NEOs. Upon retirement or separation from service for other reasons, NEOs are entitled to certain accrued benefits and payments
generally available to other employees. We describe these benefits and payments in the &#147;Pension Benefits Table,&#148; the &#147;Nonqualified Deferred Compensation Table&#148; and the &#147;Potential Payments Upon Termination or <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Change-in-Control&#148;</FONT></FONT> table in this Proxy Statement. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP BGCOLOR="#284993"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#ffffff">&nbsp;&nbsp;EXECUTIVE&nbsp;COMPENSATION&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD></TR></TABLE> <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Compensation Recovery Policies</B>
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The Chevron Incentive Plan, Long-Term Incentive Plan, Deferred Compensation Plan for Management Employees, Retirement Restoration Plan, and
Employee Savings Investment Plan&#150;Restoration Plan include provisions permitting us to &#147;claw back&#148; certain amounts of cash and equity awarded to an NEO at any time if the NEO engages in certain acts of misconduct, including, among
other things: embezzlement; fraud or theft; disclosure of confidential information or other acts that harm our business, reputation or employees; misconduct resulting in Chevron having to prepare an accounting restatement; and failure to abide by
post-termination agreements respecting confidentiality, noncompetition or nonsolicitation. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Tax
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Gross-Ups</FONT></B> </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">We do not pay tax <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">gross-ups</FONT> to our NEOs. We do
provide standard expatriate packages, which include tax equalization payments, to all employees of the Company who serve on overseas assignments, including executive officers. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Tax Deductibility of NEO Compensation</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">We have structured our CIP and certain LTIP awards with the intention of meeting the requirements for deductibility under Section 162(m) of the Internal
Revenue Code, which permits Chevron to deduct certain compensation paid to our CEO and other three most highly paid executives (excluding our Chief Financial Officer) if such compensation in excess of $1&nbsp;million is performance-based. Although
the MCC considers the deductibility of the compensation of our executives, in order to maintain flexibility and retain and motivate our executive officers, it does not require all compensation to be deductible. For example, the portion of the base
salaries in excess of $1&nbsp;million for our covered officers is not deductible; however, the MCC considers these salaries to be in the best interests of Chevron and its stockholders. Further, time-based RSUs are not qualified under Section 162(m)
and therefore are not deductible. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt">We explain the amount of salary and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-equity</FONT> incentive plan compensation in
proportion to total compensation in our &#147;Compensation Discussion and Analysis&#151;Pay Philosophy and Plan Design.&#148; </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(2)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt">Amounts for each fiscal year reflect the aggregate grant date fair value of performance shares and restricted stock
units (RSUs) granted under the Long-Term Incentive Plan of Chevron Corporation (LTIP) on January&nbsp;27, 2016. We calculate the grant date fair value of these awards in accordance with Financial Accounting Standards Board Accounting Standards
Codification Topic 718, Compensation&#151;Stock Compensation (ASC Topic 718), as described in Note 23, &#147;Stock Options and Other Share-Based Compensation,&#148; to the Consolidated Financial Statements contained in our Annual Report on Form <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10-K</FONT> for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2016. These RSUs and performance shares do not accrue dividends or dividend equivalents. For purposes of this table only, estimates of forfeitures related to service-based
vesting conditions for awards have been disregarded. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt">For performance shares granted on January&nbsp;27, 2016, the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">per-share</FONT> grant
date fair value was $73.34. We use a Monte Carlo approach to calculate estimated grant date fair value. To derive estimated grant date fair value per share, this valuation technique simulates total shareholder return (TSR) for the Company and our
LTIP Performance Share Peer Group (BP, ExxonMobil, Royal Dutch Shell, and Total) using market data for a period equal to the term of the performance period, correlates the simulated returns within the peer group to estimate a probable payout value,
and discounts the probable payout value using a risk-free rate for Treasury bonds having a term equal to the performance period. Performance shares are paid in cash, and the cash payout, if any, is based on market conditions at the end of the
performance period (January 2016 through December 2018). Payout is calculated in the manner described in Footnote 2 to the &#147;Option Exercises and Stock Vested in Fiscal Year 2016&#148; table in this Proxy Statement. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt">For Mr.&nbsp;Wirth, the 2016 amount also includes the aggregate grant date fair value of RSUs granted under the LTIP on
January&nbsp;27, 2016. The <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">per-unit</FONT> grant date fair value of the restricted stock units was $83.29, the closing price of Chevron common stock on the grant date. These RSUs are paid in cash upon vesting and are
payable following the third annual anniversary of the grant date. Total payout will be based on the Chevron common stock closing price on the vesting date. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP BGCOLOR="#284993"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#ffffff">&nbsp;&nbsp;EXECUTIVE&nbsp;COMPENSATION&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD></TR></TABLE> <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt">The material terms of performance shares and RSUs granted in 2016 are described in the &#147;Grants of Plan-Based
Awards in Fiscal Year 2016&#148; and &#147;Outstanding Equity Awards at 2016 Fiscal <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Year-End&#148;</FONT> tables in this Proxy Statement. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(3)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt">Amounts for each fiscal year reflect the aggregate grant date fair value of nonstatutory/nonqualified stock options
granted under the LTIP on January&nbsp;27, 2016. The <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">per-option</FONT> grant date fair value was $9.53. We calculate the grant date fair value of these stock options in accordance with ASC Topic 718, as described in
Note 23, &#147;Stock Options and Other Share-Based Compensation,&#148; to the Consolidated Financial Statements contained in our Annual Report on Form <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10-K</FONT> for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2016. Stock
options do not accrue dividends or dividend equivalents. For purposes of this table only, estimates of forfeitures related to service-based vesting conditions for awards have been disregarded. The material terms of stock options granted in 2016 are
described in the &#147;Grants of Plan-Based Awards in Fiscal Year 2016&#148; and &#147;Outstanding Equity Awards at 2016 Fiscal <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Year-End&#148;</FONT> tables in this Proxy Statement. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(4)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt">2016 amounts reflect Chevron Incentive Plan (CIP) awards for the 2016 performance year that were paid in March 2017.
The following NEOs elected to defer portions of their awards to the DCP as follows: Mr.&nbsp;Watson, 25&nbsp;percent, or $524,100; and Ms.&nbsp;Yarrington, 1&nbsp;percent, or $8,901. See &#147;Compensation Discussion and Analysis&#151;Components of
Executive Compensation&#151;Annual Incentive Plan (Chevron Incentive Plan)&#148; for a detailed description of CIP awards. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(5)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt">2016 amounts represent the aggregate change in the actuarial present value of the NEO&#146;s pension value for the
Chevron Retirement Plan (CRP) and the Chevron Retirement Restoration Plan (RRP) from January&nbsp;1, 2016, through December&nbsp;31, 2016, expressed as a lump sum. (The Deferred Compensation Plan for Management Employees and Deferred Compensation
Plan for Management Employees II (both, the DCP) and ESIP Restoration Plan <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">(ESIP-RP)</FONT> do not pay above-market or preferential earnings and are not represented in this table.) For purposes of this disclosure, we
have used the same amounts required to be disclosed in the &#147;Pension Benefits Table&#148; in this Proxy Statement. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt">2016 changes in the actuarial present value of an NEO&#146;s pension value are attributable to five factors.
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Arial; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:7.5pt"><B>Increases in highest average earnings (HAE) </B></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt">HAE is the highest consecutive <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">36-month</FONT> average base salary and CIP awards.
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Arial; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:7.5pt"><B>Interest and discount rate assumptions used to estimate the value of the benefit </B></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt">Generally, a higher interest rate produces a lower pension value, and a lower interest rate produces a higher pension
value. The lump sum interest rates for determining the actuarial present values of the pension benefit are based on the Pension Protection Act of 2006 lump sum interest rates, and such rates are lower in 2016 than those used in 2015. In addition,
2016&#146;s discount rate, 3.9&nbsp;percent, is lower than 2015&#146;s discount rate, 4.0&nbsp;percent. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Arial; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:7.5pt"><B>An additional year of age </B></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt">The Chevron Retirement Plan and Retirement Restoration Plan provide an unreduced benefit at age 60 for eligible
participants. Generally, being a year older results in an increase in pension value due to a shorter discount period from the current age to the assumed retirement age of 60. Once an NEO reaches age 60, the discount rate no longer applies.
Furthermore, the pension value can be negatively impacted when the assumed duration of future payments is shorter based on age and actuarial assumptions. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Arial; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:7.5pt"><B>An additional year of benefit service earned in 2016 </B></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt">All of the NEOs worked for a full year in 2016, and their pension benefits increased because they earned an additional
year of benefit service. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Arial; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:7.5pt"><B>Mortality projections </B></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt">When mortality tables project longer life spans, pension benefits increase. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7.5pt">The following table provides a breakdown of the percent change in the NEO&#146;s pension values: </P></TD></TR></TABLE>

<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#284993"><B><SUB STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:bottom"></SUB></B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#284993"><I>Chevron Corporation&#151;2017 Proxy Statement</I></FONT><FONT

<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV ALIGN="right">
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="70%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="26%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>

<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
