<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="font-size:1pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:18.5pt">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="91%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:20pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5e5e5"> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18.5pt; font-family:Arial"><A NAME="xtoc304635_62"></A><B>Board Proposal to Determine,
on an Advisory Basis, the Frequency of Future Advisory Votes on Named Executive Officer Compensation</B> <FONT STYLE="font-family:arial"><I></I></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:20pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial"><I>(Item 4 on the Proxy Card)</I></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:16pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">As described in Item&nbsp;3, our stockholders are being asked to vote to approve the compensation of the
Company&#146;s named executive officers as disclosed in the Compensation Discussion and Analysis, the accompanying compensation tables, and the related narrative disclosure in this Proxy Statement. As required by Section&nbsp;14A of the Securities
Exchange Act of 1934, stockholders are also entitled to vote, on an advisory basis, as to whether future advisory votes on named executive officer compensation should occur every year, every two years, or every three years or to abstain from such
voting. Our stockholders voted on a similar proposal in 2011 with the majority voting to hold the advisory vote
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
on named executive officer compensation every year, and we have conducted such an annual vote since that time. After careful consideration, the Board of Directors recommends that future advisory
votes on named executive officer compensation continue to occur every year. The Board believes that this is the appropriate frequency so stockholders may annually express their views on our named executive officer compensation program. The Board
values the opportunity to receive feedback and will consider the outcome of these votes in making compensation decisions. </P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:24pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B><A NAME="xtoc304635_63"></A>Vote Required</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:16pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Stockholders can specify one of four choices for this proposal on the proxy card: one year, two years, three years, or abstain. Stockholders are not
voting to approve or disapprove the Board&#146;s recommendation. This advisory vote on the frequency of future advisory votes on named executive officer compensation is non-binding on the Board of Directors. Notwithstanding the Board&#146;s
recommendation and the outcome of the stockholder vote, the Board may in the future decide to conduct advisory votes on a more or less frequent basis and may vary its practice based on factors such as discussions with stockholders and the adoption
of material changes to compensation programs. The Board will disclose its position on the frequency of future advisory votes on named executive officer compensation as part of our corporate governance disclosures on our website at
<I>www.chevron.com</I>. Engagement with our stockholders is a key component of our corporate governance, and we will continue to engage with our stockholders during the period between advisory votes. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B><A NAME="xtoc304635_64"></A>Your Board&#146;s Recommendation</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:16pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993">Your Board recommends that you vote, on an advisory basis, to conduct future advisory votes on named executive officer compensation every year.
</FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD WIDTH="91%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:20pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5e5e5"> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:20pt; font-family:Arial"><A NAME="xtoc304635_65"></A><A NAME="xtoc304635_66"></A><B>Rule
14a-8 Stockholder Proposals</B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:16pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Your Board welcomes dialogue on the topics presented in the Rule 14a-8 stockholder proposals on the
following pages. Chevron strives to communicate proactively and transparently on these and other issues of interest to the Company and its stockholders. Some of the following stockholder proposals may contain assertions about Chevron that we believe
are incorrect. Your Board has not attempted to refute all such assertions. However, your Board has considered each proposal and recommended a vote based on the specific reasons set forth in each Board response. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">We received a number of proposals requesting specific reports. As a general principle, your Board opposes developing specially requested reports because
producing them is a poor use of Chevron&#146;s resources when the issues are addressed sufficiently through existing communications. Moreover, your Board believes
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
that stockholders benefit from reading about these issues in the context of Chevron&#146;s other activities rather than in isolation. Many of the issues raised in the following stockholder
proposals are discussed in Chevron&#146;s Corporate Responsibility Report, our Annual Report, and this Proxy Statement. Additional information on Chevron&#146;s corporate governance and corporate social responsibility philosophies and initiatives is
available on our website at <I>www.chevron.com</I>. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Your Board urges stockholders to read this Proxy Statement, the Annual Report, and the Corporate
Responsibility Report, as well as the other information presented on Chevron&#146;s website. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">We will provide the name, address, and share ownership
of the stockholders who submitted a Rule 14a-8 stockholder proposal upon a stockholder&#146;s request. </P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:24pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><A NAME="xtoc304635_66"></A><A NAME="xtoc304635_67"></A><B>Vote Required</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:16pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Stockholder proposals are approved if the number of shares voted FOR exceeds the number of shares voted AGAINST. Any shares not voted on these proposals
(whether by abstention or otherwise) will have no impact on these proposals. If you are a street name stockholder and do not vote your shares, your bank, broker, or other holder of record <U>cannot</U> vote your shares at its discretion on these
proposals. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><A NAME="xtoc304635_68"></A><B>Your Board&#146;s Recommendation</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:16pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993">Your Board recommends that you vote </FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"><B>AGAINST</B></FONT><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993"> each of the stockholder proposals on the following pages. </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP BGCOLOR="#284993"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#ffffff">&nbsp;&nbsp;STOCKHOLDER&nbsp;PROPOSALS&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD></TR></TABLE> <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:22pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><A NAME="xtoc304635_69"></A><B>Stockholder Proposal&nbsp;Regarding Report on Lobbying</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:22pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993"><I>(Item&nbsp;5 on the Proxy Card)</I></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:36pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial"><B>Whereas</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">, we believe in full
disclosure of Chevron&#146;s direct and indirect lobbying activities and expenditures to assess whether Chevron&#146;s lobbying is consistent with its expressed goals and in the best interests of stockholders. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial"><B>Resolved</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">, the stockholders of Chevron Corp. (&#147;Chevron&#148;) request
the preparation of a report, updated annually, disclosing: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="16" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">1.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Company policy and procedures governing lobbying, both direct and indirect, and grassroots lobbying communications.
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="16" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">2.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Payments by Chevron used for (a)&nbsp;direct or indirect lobbying or (b)&nbsp;grassroots lobbying communications, in each
case including the amount of the payment and the recipient. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="16" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">3.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Chevron&#146;s membership in and payments to any tax-exempt organization that writes and endorses model legislation.
</P></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="16" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">4.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Description of management&#146;s and the Board&#146;s decision making process and oversight for making payments described
in sections 2 and 3 above. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">For purposes of this proposal, a &#147;grassroots lobbying communication&#148; is a communication
directed to the general public that (a)&nbsp;refers to specific legislation or regulation, (b)&nbsp;reflects a view on the legislation or regulation and (c)&nbsp;encourages the recipient of the communication to take action with respect to the
legislation or regulation. &#147;Indirect lobbying&#148; is lobbying engaged in by a trade association or other organization of which Chevron is a member. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Both &#147;direct and indirect lobbying&#148; and &#147;grassroots lobbying communications&#148; include efforts at the local, state and federal levels.
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The report shall be presented to the Audit Committee or other relevant oversight committees and posted on Chevron&#146;s website.
</P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="justify"><B>Supporting Statement </B></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.5pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">We encourage transparency and accountability in Chevron&#146;s use of corporate funds to influence
legislation and regulation. Lobbying by oil companies on climate is increasingly under scrutiny (&#147;Threatened Oil Industry Rethinks Climate Stance,&#148; <I>Politico</I>, July&nbsp;11, 2016). Chevron spent $15.48 million in 2014 and 2015 on
federal lobbying (opensecrets.org). These figures do not include lobbying expenditures to influence legislation in states, where Chevron also lobbies but disclosure is uneven or absent. For example, Chevron spent $8.289 million lobbying in
California for 2014 and 2015, and Chevron&#146;s lobbying on California&#146;s greenhouse gas reduction bill has attracted media attention (&#147;How Big Oil Spent $10m to Defeat California Climate Change Legislation,&#148; <I>The Guardian</I>,
February&nbsp;5, 2016). </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Chevron is a member of the American Petroleum Institute, Business Roundtable and Western States Petroleum Association. In
2015, Chevron made a $500,000 political contribution to the
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
Chamber of Commerce, which has spent more than $1.2 billion on lobbying since 1998. Chevron does not disclose its memberships in, or payments to, trade associations, or the amounts used for
lobbying. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">And Chevron does not disclose membership in or contributions to tax-exempt organizations that write and endorse model legislation, such as
being a member of the American Legislative Exchange Council (ALEC). Chevron&#146;s ALEC membership continues to draw press scrutiny (&#147;Chevron Plays Kick the Can,&#148; <I>Huffington Post</I>, May&nbsp;31, 2016). Over 100 companies have publicly
left ALEC, including BP, ConocoPhillips, Occidental Petroleum and Shell. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Transparent reporting would reveal whether company assets are being used for
objectives contrary to Chevron&#146;s long-term interests. </P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="96%"></TD></TR>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="right"><B>64</B></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B></B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993"><I>Chevron Corporation&#151;2017 Proxy Statement</I></FONT><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B></B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV ALIGN="right">
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="70%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="26%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="25%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#284993">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP ALIGN="right" BGCOLOR="#284993"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#ffffff">&nbsp;&nbsp;STOCKHOLDER&nbsp;PROPOSALS&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Board of Directors&#146; Response</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Your Board recommends a vote AGAINST this proposal because the Board believes that a
special report beyond Chevron&#146;s current voluntary and mandatory disclosures is an unnecessary and inefficient use of Chevron&#146;s resources. Chevron already discloses to the public extensive information about its political contributions and
lobbying activities. In many cases, this disclosure goes beyond what is required by law. At Chevron&#146;s last five Annual Meetings, an average of 75&nbsp;percent of votes cast opposed this proposal. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Energy&#151;its production, development, deployment, and consumption&#151;is one of the most important public policy issues today, both
domestically and internationally. Public policy decisions can significantly affect Chevron&#146;s operations, strategies, and stockholder value. Opponents of our industry are well resourced to influence policy decisions in a manner that achieves
their objectives. Accordingly, to protect stockholder value, Chevron exercises its fundamental right and responsibility to participate in the political process and to ensure lawmakers have the benefit of our expertise. We do so by engaging in direct
and indirect lobbying, making political contributions to candidates and entities who support oil and gas industry development, and participating in various business and policy organizations that advocate positions designed to support free markets
and fair energy industry legislation and regulations. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Chevron has an established practice to determine which public policy issues
are important to the Company&#146;s long-term interests. We may not agree with every position taken by the industry or the trade associations we support, but by participating in these organizations, we have the best opportunity to influence their
positions in a manner that aligns with our values and the long-term interests of our stockholders. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Chevron management adheres to the
highest ethical standards when engaging in political activities, ensures that such activities align with corporate goals, and complies with the letter and spirit of all laws and regulations governing lobbying activities and disclosure. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Chevron agrees that transparency and accountability are important aspects of corporate political activity. That is why Chevron provides
extensive disclosure of its political activities. At <I>www.chevron.com/investors/corporate-governance /political-contributions</I>, stockholders and the public can find: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="10">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="8" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Information about Chevron&#146;s political contributions, lobbying philosophy and oversight mechanisms.
</P></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Chevron&#146;s most recent annual Corporate Political Contributions report and the Chevron Employee Political Action
Committee (CEPAC) Contributions report. Itemized in each report are the contributions to all candidates, organizations, and committees as well as the ballot measures that received contributions designated specifically for political involvement.
</P></TD>
<TD WIDTH="8">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Chevron&#146;s prior-year federal quarterly lobbying reports and a link to the federal lobbying disclosure website, which
contains current and previous years&#146; reports </P></TD>
<TD WIDTH="8">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-right:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">(<I>http://disclosures.house.gov/ld/ldsearch.aspx</I>). These reports disclose
total corporate expenditures related to lobbying and issues lobbied. The Company&#146;s lobbying activities in the United States are strictly regulated by federal, state, and local lobbying laws. Each governing jurisdiction determines its own
regulations regarding lobbying compliance and also establishes the policies and guidelines associated with reporting and disclosure. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">A link to the federal lobbying contributions search website. This site contains the details of the Company&#146;s current
and previous years&#146; contributions. There is also a link to the Federal Election Commission website, which contains current and previous years&#146; reports for the CEPAC. </P></TD>
<TD WIDTH="8">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">A link to the California State Lobbying Activity site, which contains the Company&#146;s prior-year California quarterly
lobbying reports. </P></TD>
<TD WIDTH="8">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Chevron&#146;s political activities are subject to thorough review and oversight. All corporate
political contributions are centrally controlled, budgeted, and reviewed for compliance with the law. Each contribution is reported in its applicable jurisdiction. The Public Policy Committee of the Board annually reviews the policies, procedures
and expenditures for Chevron&#146;s political activities, including political contributions and direct and indirect lobbying. In addition, Chevron&#146;s employees are required to complete political and lobbying compliance training. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Your Board is confident that the Company&#146;s political activities are aligned with its stockholders&#146; long-term interests. The
Board encourages you to review the reports and other materials described above and on Chevron&#146;s website and to judge for yourself whether Chevron&#146;s efforts and your interests are aligned. Given the current extensive disclosure described
above, the Board believes the preparation and the publication of the report called for in this proposal are unnecessary. </P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Therefore, your Board recommends that you vote AGAINST this proposal.
</B></FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="70%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="25%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="26%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP BGCOLOR="#284993"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#ffffff">&nbsp;&nbsp;STOCKHOLDER&nbsp;PROPOSALS&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD></TR></TABLE> <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:22pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Stockholder Proposal Regarding Report
on Business with Conflict-Complicit Governments</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993"><I> </I></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:22pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993"><I>(Item&nbsp;6 on the Proxy Card) </I></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:36pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial"><B>Whereas: </B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">Chevron, in
partnership with Total, the Petroleum Authority of Thailand, and Myanmar Oil and Gas Enterprise (MOGE), holds equity in one of the largest investment projects in Burma (Myanmar): the Yadana gas-field and pipeline that generates billions of dollars
for the Burmese government. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">In 2005, Chevron acquired Unocal along with the legal, moral, and political liabilities of its investment in
Burma. Human rights organizations documented egregious human rights abuses by Burmese troops employed to secure the Yadana pipeline area, including forcible relocation of villagers and use of forced labor. In March 2005, Unocal settled a case for a
reported multi-million dollar amount in which it was claimed that Unocal was complicit in human rights abuses by Burmese troops hired by the Yadana project to provide security. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">In Burma, foreign participation in the energy sector takes place through joint ventures with the state-owned Myanmar Oil and Gas Enterprise (MOGE). U.S.
lawmakers, including Sen. John McCain and former Sen. Joseph Lieberman, have described their concerns that &#147;MOGE&#146;s operations lack transparency, that it remains overly influenced by the Burmese military, and that the large amounts of
foreign investment flowing into MOGE are not sufficiently accountable to the Burmese people or its parliament.&#148; </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">In March 2015, Chevron entered
into an additional Production Sharing Contract with MOGE to explore for oil and gas in the Rakhine Basin. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Rakhine State is home to the Rohingya
people, an ethnic minority subject to a government-sanctioned campaign of repression and
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
violence. Despite often having lived in Burma for generations, the Rohingya are denied citizenship, freedom of religion, and voting rights. In 2012, Burmese security forces moved more than
120,000 Rohingya from their homes into detention camps where access is restricted to basic services, such as food, healthcare, and education. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">In late
November 2016, the U.N.&#145;s human rights agency said that abuses suffered by the Rohingya may amount to crimes against humanity. The U.S. Holocaust Memorial Museum has reported that the Rohingya are &#147;at grave risk of additional mass
atrocities and even genocide.&#148; </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The International Coalition for the Responsibility to Protect (ICRtoP) monitors countries worldwide for instances
of serious crimes under international law including genocide, war crimes, ethnic cleansing, and crimes against humanity. In this regard, ICRtoP lists several countries, cited by the United Nations and civil society organizations, in which Chevron is
currently producing oil and gas: Burma (Myanmar), Democratic Republic of Congo, and Nigeria. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial"><B>Be it resolved:
</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">The shareholders request the Board to publish a report six months following the 2017 annual general meeting, omitting proprietary information and prepared at reasonable cost, evaluating the feasibility of
adopting a policy of not doing business with governments that are complicit in genocide and/or crimes against humanity. </FONT></P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="justify"><B>Supporting Statement </B></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.5pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">As shareholders, we believe that our company has the duty to avoid the moral, legal, financial,
reputational, and operational risks
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
posed by doing business with governments complicit in genocide or crimes against humanity.
</P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">

<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B></B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993"><I>Chevron Corporation&#151;2017 Proxy Statement</I></FONT><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B></B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV ALIGN="right">
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="70%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="26%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="25%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#284993">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP ALIGN="right" BGCOLOR="#284993"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#ffffff">&nbsp;&nbsp;STOCKHOLDER&nbsp;PROPOSALS&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Board of Directors&#146; Response</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Your Board recommends a vote AGAINST this proposal because Chevron has in place rigorous
policies and processes to identify and manage geopolitical and socioeconomic issues and risks. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Chevron conducts its business in
accordance with The Chevron Way values, which place the highest priority on conducting our business in a socially and environmentally responsible manner, respecting the law, supporting universal human rights, and maintaining the highest ethical
standards. We reinforce our commitment and manage corporate responsibility-related risks through our management systems, corporate policies, and corporate responsibility performance. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Chevron&#146;s Human Rights Policy clarifies and reinforces our responsibility to respect human rights, focusing on areas most salient to
our business: employees, security, community engagement, and suppliers. Related processes and guidance provide direction on management of potential human rights issues such as resettlement, grievances, and dealings with indigenous peoples. Our
policy addresses labor relations, contracting and procurement, stakeholder engagement, and environmental protection. The policy calls for assessments of security and human rights issues in areas of operations, consistent with the Voluntary
Principles on Security and Human Rights (Voluntary Principles). </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Chevron&#146;s Corporate Policy on Security of Personnel and Assets
(SP&amp;A) supplements and reinforces our Human Rights Policy. This policy explains the link between security and human rights and establishes guidelines and safeguards to help Chevron conduct security operations in compliance with our Human Rights
Policy and applicable national and international law. The SP&amp;A is part of Chevron&#146;s Operational Excellence Management System (OEMS). A detailed description of our OEMS is available at
<I><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">https://www.chevron.com/about/operational-excellence/oems</FONT></I>. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">A key aspect of
Chevron&#146;s security process is the Security Risk Assessment Program, which includes an assessment tool to help business units identify, assess, and manage potential security and human rights issues. This assessment considers matters related to
community grievances, violence and conflict, security forces, and equipment transfer, among others. Issue assessments are conducted prior to the commencement of a major new project or entry into sensitive operating environments. Chevron requires
reporting of security and human rights incidents to Chevron&#146;s Global Security group and
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
other human rights concerns to the Public Policy and Corporate Responsibility group. Chevron offers a global 24-hour hotline for employees, contractors, and external stakeholders to report
complaints in numerous languages via phone, Internet, or email. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:3pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Chevron&#146;s standard security services contracts incorporate its
commitment to the Voluntary Principles. In particular, our contractual terms set forth expectations regarding training on the Voluntary Principles, background screening of contract personnel, and investigation of allegations of security and human
rights incidents. Our contracts also reserve the right for Chevron to audit contracting companies to determine if they adhere to these and other requirements. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:3pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Our Enterprise Risk Management Process includes an annual review with executive management and the Board of Directors that identifies
financial, operational, market, political, and other risks inherent in our business. The Board oversees Chevron&#146;s risk management policies and practices to ensure that the appropriate systems are employed. The Board&#146;s Public Policy
Committee monitors social, political, environmental, human rights, and public policy aspects of Chevron&#146;s business and the communities in which it operates, including in Myanmar. Semiannually, the Board receives a report that discusses
legislative and regulatory initiatives, safety and environmental stewardship, community relations, and reputational issues for key countries where Chevron operates. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:3pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">For more than 20 years, Chevron, through its subsidiary Unocal Myanmar Offshore Co, Ltd. (UMOL), has worked with its joint venture
partners in Myanmar to promote economic growth and development. Chevron is committed to operating responsibly in Myanmar, in accordance with The Chevron Way values, which apply everywhere the Company operates. Comprehensive social and community
impact assessments for the offshore Myanmar exploration program are outlined in a public report submitted by UMOL to the U.S. government in 2016, available at
<I>http://photos.state.gov/libraries/burma/895/pdf/Chevron%20Myanmar%20Responsible%20Investment% 20Report_24May2016.pdf</I>. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:3pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">With
The Chevron Way values as our foundation, we believe the framework of management systems, policies and processes that we use to guide our business decisions wherever we operate provides clear and consistent guidance and expectations for our
investments and operational decisions. The proposed feasibility review is unnecessary, as it would not improve Chevron&#146;s current procedures for evaluating and managing in-country issues and risks.
</P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Therefore, your Board recommends that you vote AGAINST this proposal.</B>
</FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP BGCOLOR="#284993"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#ffffff">&nbsp;&nbsp;STOCKHOLDER&nbsp;PROPOSALS&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD></TR></TABLE> <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:22pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Stockholder Proposal Regarding Climate Change Stress Testing and Scenario
Impact</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993"><I></I></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"> </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:22pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993"><I>(Item&nbsp;7 on the Proxy Card) </I></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:36pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial"><B>Resolved</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">: Shareholders
request that by the Annual Meeting of Stockholders in 2018, Chevron Corporation (Chevron), with board oversight publishes an annual assessment of long-term portfolio impacts to 2035 of plausible climate change scenarios, at reasonable cost and
omitting proprietary information. The report should explain how capital planning and business strategies incorporate analyses of the short- and long-term financial risks of
</FONT></P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
a lower-carbon economy. Specifically, the report should outline impacts of multiple, fluctuating demand and price scenarios on the company&#146;s existing reserves and resource
portfolio&#151;including the International Energy Agency&#146;s &#147;450 Scenario,&#148; which sets out an energy pathway consistent with the internationally recognized goal of limiting global increase in temperature to 2 degrees Celsius.
</P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="justify"><B>Supporting Statement </B></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.5pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Climate change, and actions to mitigate and adapt to it, will meaningfully affect the demand for, and costs
associated with, finding, extracting, refining and selling carbon-based fuels, therefore impacting shareholder value. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Recognizing the economic and
political risks associated with climate change, the probability of strong climate change-related policy action has increased since the Paris Agreement reached at the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change Conference of the Parties
(COP21) in December 2015. COP21 concluded with 195 countries agreeing to keep global temperature increase &#147;well below&#148; 2 degrees Celsius, and pursuing efforts to limit it to 1.5 degrees Celsius. Significantly, the two largest greenhouse
gas emitters globally, the United States and China, ratified this agreement in 2016. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Investors require better transparency on the resilience of
Chevron&#146;s portfolios under different scenarios based on these and likely future developments. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Chevron has recognized in its Securities and
Exchange Commission filings and sustainability reporting that policies, regulations and actions that place a price on greenhouse gas emissions&#151;or affect the supply and demand for hydrocarbons&#151;could have a significant impact on its
business. The increasing likelihood of public policy action and viability of technological advancements aimed at addressing climate change make it vital
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
that Chevron provide investors with more detailed analyses of the potential risks to its business, under a range of scenarios. While Chevron provides some indication that &#147;consideration of
greenhouse gas issues, climate change related risks and carbon pricing risks are integrated into its strategy, business planning, risk management tools and processes,&#148; it has not presented sufficiently detailed analyses of how it stress tests
its portfolio of new and existing projects under various carbon-constrained scenarios. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">This contrasts with Chevron&#146;s competitors, including:
</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Ten oil and gas companies announcing their shared ambition to limit the global average temperature rise to 2 degrees
Celsius (Oil and Gas Climate Initiative); </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Shell, BP, and Statoil endorsing the &#147;Strategic Resilience for 2035 and Beyond&#148; shareholder resolutions that
received almost unanimous support in 2015; Suncor endorsing a similar resolution with overwhelming support in 2016; </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">ConocoPhillips and Total testing capital planning decisions against multiple carbon-constrained scenarios and disclosing
the results. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Publication of the requested report will demonstrate that Chevron is strategically planning to remain competitive in a
carbon-constrained future and generate continued value for shareholders. </P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">

<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B></B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993"><I>Chevron Corporation&#151;2017 Proxy Statement</I></FONT><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B></B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV ALIGN="right">
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="70%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="26%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="25%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#284993">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP ALIGN="right" BGCOLOR="#284993"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#ffffff">&nbsp;&nbsp;STOCKHOLDER&nbsp;PROPOSALS&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Board of Directors&#146; Response</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;
</P><div style="width:100%;margin-left:0%; margin-right:0%;background-color:#e5e5e5;padding-top:2pt;padding-bottom:3pt"><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Your Board recommends a vote AGAINST this proposal because we believe that the report
&#147;Managing Climate Change Risks: A Perspective for Investors,&#148; published on March&nbsp;8, 2017, substantially addresses the issues raised by the Proponent and that further reporting is unnecessary. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Chevron shares the concerns of governments and the public about climate change risks and recognizes that the use of fossil fuels to meet
the world&#146;s energy needs is a contributor to rising levels of greenhouse gases (GHGs) in the earth&#146;s atmosphere. Chevron believes that taking prudent, practical, and cost-effective action to address climate change risks is the right thing
to do.&nbsp;Mitigation of GHG emissions, adaptation to climate change, and continuation of scientific and technological research should all be considered. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">In response to the 2016 vote of stockholders on a substantially similar proposal, and in the context of our ongoing risk management,
strategy, and planning activities, we have assessed and reported on the impact of carbon-constrained scenarios. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Our report
discusses: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="10">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="8" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Chevron&#146;s view of fundamentals impacting our long-term planning, including energy&#146;s role in economic growth and
social progress, views of long-term energy supply and demand, and how those views could vary with climate policy; </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="10">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="8" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">well-established third-party views of supply and demand under a variety of scenarios, including those under the
International Energy Agency&#146;s 450 Case; </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="10">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="8" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">the various risk management processes we utilize and the related governance &#151; both by executive management and the
Board &#151; for these processes, including the management of a dynamic portfolio;
</P></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">climate-specific risks and the processes we have undertaken and would undertake for managing these for our existing
upstream producing assets, existing downstream and chemicals businesses, upstream assets held but not yet sanctioned for development, and possible future resources not yet acquired; </P></TD>
<TD WIDTH="8">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">actions undertaken by Chevron to reduce, and progress in reducing, GHG emissions; and </P></TD>
<TD WIDTH="8">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">the voluntary disclosures we already make relating to our GHG emissions. </P></TD>
<TD WIDTH="8">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Upon examination of the different supply-and-demand scenarios, it is clear that a decrease in
overall fossil fuel-related GHG emissions is not inconsistent with continued or increased production <I>by the most efficient producers</I>.&nbsp;The premise that governmental or societal responses to climate change require each fossil fuel producer
to curtail its individual production proportionately is flawed and unrealistic and, if carried out, could impose great economic inefficiency. We believe that Chevron is a capable and efficient producer, well positioned to compete in any plausible
supply-and-demand scenario. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Your Board encourages you to read the complete report on Chevron.com and learn more about
Chevron&#146;s climate risk management and about energy demand under a restrictive GHG emissions scenario at <I>www.chevron.com/climateriskperspective</I>. We will continue to update our views on the website and in regulatory filings as appropriate.
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The Company has processes in place involving executive management and the Board by which we manage a variety of risks to our
business, including climate-related risks.&nbsp;The Board&#146;s assessment is that Chevron&#146;s existing processes are sufficient to ensure that we can monitor and adjust appropriately to likely future scenarios.
</P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
</div> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Therefore, your Board recommends that you vote AGAINST this proposal.</B>
</FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

 <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="70%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="25%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>

<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP BGCOLOR="#284993"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#ffffff">&nbsp;&nbsp;STOCKHOLDER&nbsp;PROPOSALS&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD></TR></TABLE> <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:22pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Stockholder Proposal Regarding Report
on Transition to a Low Carbon Economy</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993"><I></I></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:22pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993"><I>(Item&nbsp;8 on the Proxy Card) </I></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:36pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial"><B>Resolved</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">: Shareholders
request that Chevron issue a report (at reasonable cost, omitting proprietary information), assessing how it can respond to climate change and the resultant transition to a low carbon economy by evaluating the feasibility of altering the
company&#146;s energy mix by separating or selling off its highest carbon-risk assets, divisions, and subsidiaries, and/or buying or merging with companies with outstanding assets or technologies in low carbon or renewable energy. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial"><B>Whereas</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">: A transition toward a low carbon economy is occurring and trends to
reduce global demand for carbon-based energy are accelerating. A failure to plan for this transition may place investor capital at substantial risk. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Government policies, including fuel efficiency requirements, carbon pricing, and carbon standards are speeding the transition to a low carbon economy. The
Paris Agreement&#146;s goal of less than 2 degrees warming reinforces this transition. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Low carbon market forces, including competition from electric
cars, will be a &#147;resoundingly negative&#148; threat to the oil industry. In October 2016, Fitch Ratings urged energy companies to plan for &#147;radical change.&#148; </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The International Energy Agency states, &#147;No more than one-third of proven reserves of fossil fuels can be consumed prior to 2050 if the world is to
achieve the 2&deg; C goal.&#148; Citigroup estimates the value of unburnable fossil fuel reserves at over $100 trillion through 2050. In contrast, Carbon Tracker estimates oil majors&#146; combined upstream assets would be worth <I>$140 billion
<U>more</U></I> if restricted to projects consistent with a 2 degree demand level.
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
Under this scenario, nearly $44.8 billion of Chevron&#146;s planned capex through 2025 is at risk of stranding. (Carbon Tracker). </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Chevron&#146;s historic capital spend on high cost, high carbon assets has eroded profitability and increased Chevron&#146;s risk profile, making the
company vulnerable to a downturn in demand and a subsequent fall in oil prices. (<I>Unconventional Risks: the Growing Uncertainty of Oil Investments</I>, As You Sow 2016). </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Chevron&#146;s capital expenditures grew nearly 240 percent from 2005 to 2015. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Chevron&#146;s operating profitability has fallen 107 percent over the last decade, and </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">Chevron&#146;s 2016 ROE and ROIC are at historic lows. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Investors are concerned that Chevron is at risk of further eroding shareholder value through continuing investments in assets likely to be stranded and
uneconomic in a low carbon demand scenario. Analysts estimate that oil producers&#146; valuations could drop 40 to 60 percent under this scenario (HSBC). </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Shareholders require a plan for how Chevron will transition to a low carbon economy. Chevron&#146;s peers Total and Statoil have already begun investing
in clean energy projects including wind and solar. Other strategies may include profitably shrinking the company&#146;s carbon-based asset base. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Low
carbon planning is also critical to meeting Chevron&#146;s stated objective of increasing developing countries&#146; access to affordable and reliable energy without conflicting with the Paris Agreement
</P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="96%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="right"><B>70</B></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B></B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993"><I>Chevron Corporation&#151;2017 Proxy Statement</I></FONT><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B></B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV ALIGN="right">
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="70%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="26%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="25%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#284993">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP ALIGN="right" BGCOLOR="#284993"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#ffffff">&nbsp;&nbsp;STOCKHOLDER&nbsp;PROPOSALS&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Board of Directors&#146; Response</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;
</P><div style="width:100%;margin-left:0%; margin-right:0%;background-color:#e5e5e5;padding-top:2pt;padding-bottom:3pt"><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Your Board recommends a vote AGAINST this proposal because we believe such a report is
unnecessary in light of the safeguards and oversight in place through Chevron&#146;s strategy, planning and risk management processes. Our processes for overseeing and managing the risk of stranded assets under possible future climate change
regulation are described in &#147;Managing Climate Change Risks: A Perspective for Investors&#148;; <I>www.chevron.com/climateriskperspective</I>. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Chevron shares the concerns of governments and the public about climate change risks and recognizes that the use of fossil fuels to meet
the world&#146;s energy needs is a contributor to rising levels of greenhouse gases (GHGs) in the earth&#146;s atmosphere. Chevron believes that taking prudent, practical, and cost-effective action to address climate change risks is the right thing
to do.&nbsp;Mitigation of GHG emissions, adaptation to climate change, and continuation of scientific and technological research should all be considered. You can read more about Chevron&#146;s climate change policy principles and actions we are
taking to manage GHG emissions at <I>https://www.chevron.com/corporate-responsibility/climate-change/greenhouse-gas-management</I>. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">We disagree with the premise of the proposal that future diversification of energy sources requires all energy producers to curtail
production of fossil fuel resources and/or to diversify their portfolios proportionately. A decrease in overall fossil fuel emissions is not inconsistent with continued or increased fossil fuel production <I>by the most efficient producers</I>. We
believe Chevron is a capable and efficient energy producer, well positioned to participate in meeting future energy demand regardless of other energy sources that may become competitive. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Chevron has a variety of strategy, planning, and risk management processes and systems in place through which we test new opportunities,
evaluate our performance, and assess possible disruptors of supply and demand (including technological and regulatory) and their impact on our business.
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
Through our ongoing strategy, planning, and risk management processes, we consider portfolio and investment options that enhance our competitive position.&nbsp;This dynamic management of our
portfolio &#151; the selling and/or acquisition of assets referred to in the proposal and the timing of when we commit capital to develop various resources &#151; ensures that our Company will continue to prosper regardless of the economic or policy
environment.&nbsp;Assets deemed not having strategic fit or long-term value to us relative to others may be divested.&nbsp;Investments may be increased in areas where value is foreseen in the economic, market, and policy environments, as we have
done recently in the Permian Basin, where we have a competitive advantage.&nbsp;Another important example of our ability to respond to market signals is the increased share of natural gas production in our portfolio. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">We agree that energy from diverse sources will be needed in order to meet the growing demand for energy. As part of our ongoing planning
and assessment, we monitor and often participate in research on evolving renewable energy technologies that might impact us.&nbsp;The insights we gain are incorporated into our strategic planning.&nbsp;Based on our assessment, we believe that strong
demand for our current product slate will continue &#151; even in a carbon-constrained scenario. Given our deep and proven capability to efficiently produce hydrocarbon resources, and the important role of hydrocarbons in meeting future energy
demand, we do not believe it would be prudent to shift our hydrocarbon focus at this time. In fact, doing so could be detrimental to current stockholders because it would divert limited resources away from profitable deployment to areas where we do
not have a competitive advantage. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Chevron has robust strategy, planning, and risk management processes to ensure our portfolio mix
is appropriate, and we have made extensive disclosures on these already. Accordingly, your Board believes that the report requested in the proposal is unnecessary.
</P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
</div> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Therefore, your Board recommends that you vote AGAINST this proposal.</B>
</FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">

<TD WIDTH="96%"></TD>

 COLOR="#284993"><B></B></FONT></TD>
