<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="70%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="25%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="26%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP BGCOLOR="#284993"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#ffffff">&nbsp;&nbsp;STOCKHOLDER&nbsp;PROPOSALS&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD></TR></TABLE> <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:22pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Stockholder Proposal Regarding
Independent Chairman</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993"><I></I></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"> </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:22pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993"><I>(Item&nbsp;9 on the Proxy Card) </I></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:36pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial"><B>Resolved: </B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">The shareholders
request the Board of Directors to adopt as policy, and amend the bylaws as necessary, to require the Chair of the Board of Directors, whenever possible, to be an independent member of the Board. This policy would be phased in for the next CEO
transition. </FONT></P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">If the Board determines that a Chair who was independent when selected is no longer independent, the Board
shall select a new Chair who satisfies the requirements of the policy within a reasonable amount of time. Compliance with this policy is waived if no independent director is available and willing to serve as Chair.
</P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="justify"><B>Supporting Statement </B></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.5pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">We believe that inadequate board oversight has led management to mishandle a number of issues in ways that
significantly increase both risk and costs to shareholders. The most pressing of these issues is the ongoing legal effort by communities in Ecuador to enforce a $9.5 billion judgment against Chevron for oil pollution. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">When Chevron acquired Texaco in 2001, it acquired significant legal, financial, and reputational liabilities stemming from oil pollution of the water and
lands of communities in the Ecuadorian Amazon. For twenty years the affected communities brought suit against Texaco (and later Chevron). The case reached its conclusion in November 2013 when the Ecuadorian National Court confirmed a $9.5 billion
judgment against Chevron. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The Ecuadorian plaintiffs have initiated legal actions to seize Chevron assets in Argentina, Brazil, and Canada. In
September 2015, the Canadian Supreme Court ruled unanimously that the plaintiffs can proceed with asking Canadian courts to recognize and enforce the $9.5 billion judgment, now nearly $12 billion with statutory interest. The case is now in a Toronto
trial court awaiting decision on pre-trial motions that could determine the scope of an enforcement trial which could take place in 2017. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Chevron
management has acknowledged the serious risk to the company from enforcement of the $9.5 billion judgment. Chevron&#146;s Deputy Controller, Rex Mitchell, has testified under
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
oath that such seizures of Company assets &#147;would cause significant, irreparable damage to Chevron&#146;s business reputation and business relationships.&#148; </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">However, we believe that Chevron has yet to report adequately these risks in either public filings or statements to shareholders. Investors have requested
on several occasions that the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission investigate whether Chevron violated securities laws by misrepresenting or materially omitting information in regard to the $9.5 billion Ecuadorian judgment. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Instead of negotiating an expedient, fair, and comprehensive settlement with the affected communities in Ecuador, management has pursued a costly legal
strategy that has led to significant missteps, including moving the case from New York to Ecuador. In a move without precedent, management has harassed and subpoenaed shareholders who have questioned the Company&#146;s legal strategy. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">At Chevron&#146;s 2012 shareholder meeting 38 percent of shareholders voted in favor of this resolution. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">An independent Chair would improve board oversight of management. Therefore, please vote FOR this common-sense governance reform
</P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="96%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="right"><B>72</B></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B><SUB STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:bottom"></SUB></B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993"><I>Chevron Corporation&#151;2017 Proxy
Statement</I></FONT><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B></B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV ALIGN="right">
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="70%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="26%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="25%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#284993">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP ALIGN="right" BGCOLOR="#284993"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#ffffff">&nbsp;&nbsp;STOCKHOLDER&nbsp;PROPOSALS&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1%; font-size:22pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Board of Directors&#146; Response</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;
</P><div style="width:100%;margin-left:-1%; margin-right:-1%;background-color:#e5e5e5;padding-top:2pt;padding-bottom:3pt"><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:7.5pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Your Board recommends a vote AGAINST this proposal because the Board believes that
stockholder interests are best served when Directors have the flexibility to determine the best person to serve as Chairman, whether that person is an independent Director or the CEO. At Chevron&#146;s 2015 Annual Meeting, at which this proposal was
last considered, more than 77 percent of votes cast opposed this proposal. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:7.5pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">As required by Chevron&#146;s By-Laws, the independent
members of your Board elect the Board Chairman annually and, as part of this election, review whether to combine or separate the positions of Chairman and CEO. The Board thus has great flexibility to exercise its business judgment on behalf of
stockholders and choose the optimal leadership for the Board depending upon Chevron&#146;s particular needs and circumstances. Implementing this proposal would deprive the Board of its ability to organize and structure its functions in a manner that
is&nbsp;most effective and in the best interests of stockholders at any given&nbsp;time. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:7.5pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Your Board believes that Chevron and its
stockholders currently benefit from the unity of leadership and companywide strategic alignment associated with combining the positions of Chairman and CEO. For example, as a global energy company that negotiates concessions and leases with
host-country governments around the world, we believe it is generally advantageous to the Company for the CEO to represent the Chevron Board in such dialogues. Your Board does recognize the importance of independent oversight of the CEO and
management, and it has instituted structures and practices to enhance such oversight. When the CEO is elected Chairman, the independent Directors annually elect a Lead Director from among themselves, whose responsibilities are to: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="10">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="8" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:7.5pt">chair all meetings of the Board in the Chairman&#146;s absence, including executive sessions; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="10">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="8" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:7.5pt">serve as liaison between the Chairman and the independent Directors; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="10">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="8" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:7.5pt">consult with the Chairman on and approve meeting agendas, schedules and information sent to the Board;
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="10">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="8" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:7.5pt">consult with the Chairman on other matters pertinent to Chevron and the Board; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="10">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="8" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:7.5pt">call meetings of the independent Directors; and </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:7.5pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="10">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="8" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:7.5pt">if requested by major stockholders, be available as appropriate for consultation and direct communication.
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:7.5pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">At each Board meeting, the independent Directors meet in executive session following which the independent Lead
Director provides feedback to the Chairman. Annually, the independent Directors conduct a review of the CEO&#146;s performance. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:7.5pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">A
fixed policy requiring a separation of the roles of Chairman and CEO is also unnecessary because of Chevron&#146;s strong corporate governance practices, including: a strong independent Lead Director function, annual election of all Directors, a
majority vote requirement in uncontested elections of Directors, annual election of the Chairman by the Board, an overwhelming majority of independent Directors, proxy access, regular executive sessions for independent Directors, independent
Director access to senior management, and publicly available Corporate Governance Guidelines. This proposal erroneously implies that there is a positive correlation between long-term Company performance and separating the roles of Chairman and CEO.
Most reputable studies that have examined this question have failed to find any such correlation. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:7.5pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">For additional information
regarding the Board&#146;s views on its leadership structure, we encourage stockholders to read the &#147;Board Leadership and Independent Lead Director&#148; section of this Proxy Statement on page&nbsp;18. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:7.5pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Finally, although the proposal purports to relate to the Board&#146;s leadership structure, the supporting statement makes clear that
the
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:6pt; font-size:7.5pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
proposal is fundamentally a vehicle to discuss the Ecuador litigation and related actions against Chevron. Your Board believes that the Ecuador judgment is illegitimate and the product of fraud.
In this regard, stockholders should be aware that as part of a nearly 500-page opinion issued on March&nbsp;4, 2014, Judge Lewis&nbsp;A. Kaplan of the U.S. District Court for the Southern District of New York summarized the court&#146;s factual
findings as follows: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="83%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="9%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">&#147;[Donziger] and the Ecuadorian lawyers he led corrupted the Lago Agrio case. They submitted fraudulent evidence. They coerced one
judge, first to use a court-appointed, supposedly impartial &#145;global expert&#146; to make an overall damages assessment and then to appoint to that important role a man whom Donziger hand-picked and paid to &#145;totally play ball&#146; with the
Lago Agrio plaintiffs. They then paid a Colorado consulting firm secretly to write all or most of the global expert&#146;s report, falsely presented the report as the work of the court-appointed and supposedly impartial expert, and told half-truths
or worse to U.S. courts in attempts to prevent exposure of that and other wrongdoing. Ultimately, the [Lago Agrio Plaintiffs] team wrote the Lago Agrio court&#146;s judgment themselves and promised $500,000 to the Ecuadorian judge to rule in their
favor and sign their judgment. If ever there were a case warranting equitable relief with respect to a judgment procured by fraud, this is it.&#148;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:6pt; font-size:7.5pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">On August&nbsp;8, 2016, this 500-page trial court opinion was unanimously affirmed on appeal. The
appeals court stated that there was &#147;no basis for dismissal or reversal&#148; of the district court&#146;s judgment, noting that &#147;the record in the present case reveals a parade of corrupt actions by the [Lago Agrio Plaintiffs&#146;] legal
team including coercion, fraud and bribery, culminating in the promise to Judge Zambrano of $500,000 from a judgment in favor of the [Lago Agrio Plaintiffs].&#148; </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:6pt; font-size:7.5pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">In addition to the Second Circuit&#146;s opinion, two public prosecutors in South America have now issued opinions against enforcement
of the Ecuadorian judgment.&nbsp;On May&nbsp;13, 2015, the public prosecutor in Brazil issued a nonbinding opinion recommending to the Brazilian Superior Court of Justice that it reject the Ecuadorian plaintiffs&#146; recognition and enforcement
request, finding, among other things, that the Ecuadorian judgment was procured through fraud and corruption and cannot be recognized because it violates Brazilian and international public order.&nbsp;Similarly, on April&nbsp;19, 2016, the public
prosecutor in Argentina issued a nonbinding opinion recommending to the Argentine National Court, First Instance, that it reject the Ecuadorian plaintiffs&#146; recognition and enforcement request, finding, among other things, that enforcement of
the Ecuadorian judgment would violate Argentine public policy. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:6pt; font-size:7.5pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">On January&nbsp;20, 2017, the Ontario Superior Court of Justice
granted the motions for summary judgment submitted by Chevron Canada Limited and Chevron Corporation, ruling that the two companies are separate legal entities with separate rights and obligations.&nbsp;As a result, the court dismissed the
recognition and enforcement claim against Chevron Canada Limited. Chevron Corporation remains a defendant in the action.</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:6pt; font-size:7.5pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Your
Board expects Chevron&#146;s management to act in the best interests of the Company&#146;s stockholders and vigorously defend the Company against this fraudulent action. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:6pt; font-size:7.5pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Given strong independent Board oversight of the CEO and management and the Company&#146;s corporate governance practices, including an
effective independent Lead Director, your Board does not believe that a fixed policy requiring an independent Chairman is in the best interests of stockholders.
</P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
</div> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Therefore, your Board recommends that you vote AGAINST this proposal.</B>
</FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B><SUB STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:bottom"></SUB></B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993"><I>Chevron Corporation&#151;2017 Proxy Statement</I></FONT><FONT
 COLOR="#284993"><B></B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">73</TD></TR></TABLE>

 <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="70%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="25%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="26%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP BGCOLOR="#284993"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#ffffff">&nbsp;&nbsp;STOCKHOLDER&nbsp;PROPOSALS&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD></TR></TABLE> <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:22pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Stockholder Proposal&nbsp;Regarding
Independent</B> </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:22pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Director with Environmental Expertise</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:22pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993"><I>(Item 10 on the Proxy Card)</I></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:36pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Environmental expertise is critical to the success of companies in the energy industry because of the
significant environmental issues associated with their operations. Shareholders, lenders, host country governments and regulators, and affected communities are focused on these impacts. A company&#146;s inability to demonstrate that policies and
practices are in line with internationally accepted environmental standards can lead to difficulties in raising new capital and obtaining the necessary licences from regulators. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">We believe that Chevron would benefit by addressing the environmental impact of its business at the most strategic level by appointing an environmental
specialist to the board. An authoritative figure with acknowledged expertise and standing could perform a valuable role for [sic] by enabling Chevron to more effectively address the environmental issues inherent in its business. It would also help
ensure that the highest levels of attention focus on the development of environmental standards for new projects. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial"><B>Therefore, Be It Resolved: </B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">Shareholders request that, as elected board
directors&#146; terms of office expire, at least one candidate is recommended who: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">has a high level of expertise and experience in environmental matters relevant to hydrocarbon exploration and production
and is widely recognized in the business and environmental
</P></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

communities as an authority in such field, as reasonably determined by the company&#146;s board, and </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

director.* </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.5pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B><SUB STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:bottom"></SUB></B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993"><I>Chevron Corporation&#151;2017 Proxy
Statement</I></FONT><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B></B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV ALIGN="right">
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="70%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="26%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>

<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#284993">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP ALIGN="right" BGCOLOR="#284993"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#ffffff">&nbsp;&nbsp;STOCKHOLDER&nbsp;PROPOSALS&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:22pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Board of Directors&#146; Response</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;
</P><div style="width:100%;margin-left:0%; margin-right:0%;background-color:#e5e5e5;padding-top:2pt;padding-bottom:3pt"><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Your Board recommends a vote AGAINST this proposal because the Board believes that its
current membership possesses significant environmental experience and that as a matter of good governance, the elected members of the Board Nominating and Governance Committee should not be arbitrarily constrained in their assessment of which skills
and experience best serve the present and expected future needs of the Board. Furthermore, Chevron has rigorous standards for protecting the environment and well-developed environmental risk management systems in place. At Chevron, environmental
management is a core business function that the whole Board is responsible for overseeing in the same way it oversees performance of all other core business functions. At Chevron&#146;s seven most recent Annual Meetings, an average of 77 percent of
votes cast opposed this proposal, with opposition steadily growing over that period. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">This Proxy Statement and Chevron&#146;s
Corporate Governance Guidelines (available at <I>www.chevron.com/investors/corporate-governance</I>) discuss Chevron&#146;s Board membership criteria. These criteria include environmental experience. Your Board currently includes a number of
independent Directors with significant environmental and operational experience relevant to Chevron&#146;s business, including Directors Charles&nbsp;W. Moorman&nbsp;IV, Jon&nbsp;M. Huntsman Jr., Ronald&nbsp;D. Sugar, Alice&nbsp;P. Gast,
Inge&nbsp;G. Thulin, Linnet&nbsp;F. Deily, Robert&nbsp;E. Denham, and Dambisa F. Moyo. You can learn more about these Directors&#146; experience by reviewing their biographies in this Proxy Statement or at <I>www.chevron.com/about/leadership</I>.
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">In addition to individual experience, your Board has access to extensive internal and external expertise on environmental matters.
Your Board frequently reviews environmental matters in connection with Chevron&#146;s projects, operations, and products and is briefed by professionals whose focus is on environmental protection and stewardship. Members of the Board regularly visit
Chevron operations across the globe, where, as part of these visits, they discuss environmental matters specific and relevant to those locations. Also, in 2016, as is the case each year, the Board received a number of reports and presentations
specifically on environmental matters. Environmental professionals within Chevron have expertise at the facility, strategic, business unit and operating company levels, and Chevron routinely accesses external resources to stay apprised of best
practices and technology advances. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:4pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Chevron is committed to responsible environmental stewardship, which includes the prevention of
environmental incidents and impacts. Across its global operations, the actions of Chevron&#146;s workforce are guided by The Chevron Way and the Company&#146;s Operational Excellence Management System (OEMS) expectations. Those expectations require
the global execution of a number of corporate processes and standards, including an environmental stewardship process and a number of environmental performance standards. In 2015, Lloyd&#146;s Register Quality Assurance Ltd. attested that our OEMS
meets the requirements of the International Organization for Standardization&#146;s environmental management system standard and the Occupational Health and Safety Assessment Series&#146; management system specification and verified that the OEMS is
implemented throughout the corporation. This attestation is
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
valid for a three-year period, and work is underway for the 2018 attestation. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:4pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Our Environmental Stewardship Corporate Standard Process is our standardized approach to identify and manage potential impacts, mitigate
risks, and continually improve environmental performance. This companywide, disciplined approach helps us to identify and manage potential impacts our operations may have, such as those related to waste disposal, air emissions and water use. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:4pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Our Corporate Environmental, Social and Health Impact Assessment (ESHIA) process is applied to capital projects under Chevron&#146;s
operational control. It provides a systematic and risk-based approach to identifying, assessing, and managing potential impacts to our business including impacts to natural resources, air quality, land and water, and community health and
livelihoods. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:4pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Significant environmental and process safety issues are reviewed by the Board and management to ensure compliance with
the Company&#146;s rigorous processes and are described in Chevron&#146;s annual <I>Corporate Responsibility Report</I> and on Chevron&#146;s website. These processes have helped Chevron drive strong environmental and process safety performance. For
example, Chevron: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">is consistently executing the OEMS enterprisewide. The OEMS advances our process safety culture through engaged
leadership supported by leading and lagging metrics, technical standards, and corporate oversight; </P></TD>
<TD WIDTH="8">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">has developed and implemented WellSafe, an assurance program whose objective is to provide maximum reasonable assurance
that well control is maintained at all times on all operations that are under the direct control of the Chevron Drilling and Completions organization; </P></TD>
<TD WIDTH="8">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">has established itself as a leader among its peers in spill prevention and has reduced its recordable volume of petroleum
spills to land and water by 93 percent since 2011; </P></TD>
<TD WIDTH="8">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">has reduced its in-scope equity greenhouse gas emissions from flaring and venting by 45&nbsp;percent since 2003 and has
built and will soon operate the world&#146;s largest carbon dioxide injection facility (at the Gorgon site in Western Australia), as reported in Chevron&#146;s annual <I>Corporate Responsibility Report</I>; </P></TD>
<TD WIDTH="8">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">has an environmental management company dedicated to responsible stewardship of sites with residual environmental
impacts; and </P></TD>
<TD WIDTH="8">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="7" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">recognizes the importance of biological diversity by incorporating conservation considerations into project evaluations
and decision making and by supporting numerous flora and fauna conservation projects around the world. </P></TD>
<TD WIDTH="8">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:3pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">In light of the existing environmental experience represented on Chevron&#146;s Board and
Chevron&#146;s rigorous standards for protecting the environment and well-developed environmental risk management systems, your Board believes that this proposal is unnecessary, would narrow the pool of eligible Directors for consideration and would
provide no additional benefit to Chevron and its stockholders. </P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
</div> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Therefore, your Board recommends that you vote AGAINST this proposal.</B>
</FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="96%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B><SUB STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:bottom"></SUB></B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993"><I>Chevron Corporation&#151;2017 Proxy Statement</I></FONT><FONT
 COLOR="#284993"><B></B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">75</TD></TR></TABLE>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="70%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="25%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="26%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP BGCOLOR="#284993"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#ffffff">&nbsp;&nbsp;STOCKHOLDER&nbsp;PROPOSALS&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD></TR></TABLE> <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:22pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Stockholder Proposal&nbsp;Regarding
Special Meetings</B> </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:22pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993"><I>(Item 11 on the Proxy
Card)</I></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial" COLOR="#284993"> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:36pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial"><B>Resolved</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">: Shareowners request
that the Board of Chevron Corporation (&#147;Chevron&#148; or &#147;Company&#148;) take the steps necessary to amend Company bylaws and appropriate governing documents to give holders of 10% of outstanding common stock the power to call a special
shareowners meeting. To the fullest
</FONT></P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
extent permitted by law, such bylaw text in regard to calling a special meeting shall not contain exceptions or excluding conditions that apply only to shareowners but not to management or the
Board. </P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="justify"><B>Supporting Statement </B></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.5pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">This Proposal grants shareowners the ability to consider important matters which may arise between annual
meetings, and augments the Board&#146;s power to itself call a special meeting. This Proposal earned the support of 30% of shares voted in 2016 &#150; representing nearly $38 billion in shareholder value. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">We believe management has mishandled a variety of issues in ways that significantly increase both risk and costs to shareholders. The most pressing of
these issues is the ongoing legal effort by communities in Ecuador to enforce a $9.5 billion judgment against Chevron for oil pollution. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">When Chevron
acquired Texaco in 2001, it inherited significant legal, financial, and reputational liabilities that stemmed from pollution of the water and lands of communities in the Ecuadorian Amazon. For twenty years the affected communities brought suit
against Texaco (and subsequently Chevron). The case reached its conclusion in November 2013 when Ecuador&#146;s equivalent to the U.S. Supreme Court, the Ecuadorian National Court, confirmed a $9.5 billion judgment against Chevron. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Instead of negotiating an expedient, fair, and comprehensive settlement with the affected communities in Ecuador, Chevron pursued a costly legal strategy
that resulted in significant missteps &#150; including moving the case from New York to Ecuador. In an unprecedented move, management harassed and subpoenaed shareholders who questioned the advisability of the Company&#146;s legal strategy.
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Ecuadorian plaintiffs initiated legal actions to seize Chevron assets in Argentina, Brazil, and Canada. In
September 2015, the Canadian Supreme Court ruled <I>unanimously </I>that plaintiffs can proceed with asking Canadian courts to recognize and enforce the $9.5 billion judgment &#150; which is now nearly $12 billion with the addition of statutory
interest. The case is now in a Toronto trial court awaiting determination of pre-trial motions that could establish the scope of a 2017 enforcement trial. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Chevron&#146;s Deputy Controller, Rex Mitchell, testified under oath that such seizures of Company assets &#147;would cause significant, irreparable
damage to Chevron&#146;s business reputation and business relationships.&#148; </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">However, Chevron has yet to fully report these risks in either public
filings or statements to shareholders. As a result, investors have requested that the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission investigate whether Chevron violated securities laws by misrepresenting or materially omitting information in regard to the
multi-billion Ecuadoran judgment. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">For these reasons, shareholders need a lower threshold to call special meetings. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial"><B>Therefore: </B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">Vote FOR common-sense governance enhancements that offer
shareholders the critical right to address substantive concerns in a timely way. </FONT></P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="96%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="right"><B>76</B></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B><SUB STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:bottom"></SUB></B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#284993"><I>Chevron Corporation&#151;2017 Proxy
Statement</I></FONT><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B></B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV ALIGN="right">
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="70%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="26%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="15%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="25%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#284993">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" NOWRAP ALIGN="right" BGCOLOR="#284993"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial; " COLOR="#ffffff">&nbsp;&nbsp;STOCKHOLDER&nbsp;PROPOSALS&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1%; font-size:22pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Board of Directors&#146; Response</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;
</P><div style="width:100%;margin-left:-1%; margin-right:-1%;background-color:#e5e5e5;padding-top:2pt;padding-bottom:3pt"><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Your Board recommends a vote AGAINST this proposal because stockholders have consistently
supported Chevron&#146;s current By-Law regarding special meetings, and the Board continues to believe this By-Law is in the stockholders&#146; best interests and provides appropriate and reasonable limitations on the right to call special meetings.
In 2010, stockholders representing approximately 80&nbsp;percent of Chevron&#146;s common stock outstanding approved an amendment to Chevron&#146;s By-Laws that permits stockholders owning 15&nbsp;percent of Chevron&#146;s outstanding common stock
to call for special meetings. At Chevron&#146;s last five Annual Meetings, an average of 68&nbsp;percent of votes cast opposed this stockholder proposal to reduce the threshold for calling special meetings to 10&nbsp;percent. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Your Board continues to believe that Chevron&#146;s 15&nbsp;percent threshold to call for a special meeting provides stockholders with
assurance that a reasonable number of stockholders consider a matter important enough to merit a special meeting. Preparing for and holding a special meeting, like the Annual Meeting, is time-consuming and expensive. The 15&nbsp;percent threshold
helps avoid waste of Company and stockholder resources on addressing narrow or special interests. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">In addition to a lower threshold,
the proposal would permit a special meeting without any appropriate and reasonable limitations. Chevron&#146;s By-Laws currently contain two important limitations. A special meeting cannot be called (i)&nbsp;if the Board has already called or will
call an Annual Meeting of stockholders for the same purpose specified in the special meeting request or (ii)&nbsp;if an annual or special meeting was held not more than 12 months before the request for a special meeting was received and included the
purpose specified in the special meeting request. Given the time and cost associated with special meetings, your Board believes that these are appropriate and reasonable limitations. Moreover, the issues raised by the proponents in support of this
proposal already are consistently discussed at Chevron&#146;s Annual Meetings. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Stockholders can be assured that their right to be
apprised of and vote on significant matters is protected not only by their existing right to call for special meetings and participate in Chevron&#146;s Annual Meetings, but also by state law and other regulations. Chevron is incorporated in
Delaware, which requires that major corporate actions, such as a merger or a sale of all or substantially all of Chevron&#146;s assets, be approved by stockholders. Chevron is also listed on the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE), and the NYSE requires,
among other things, that listed companies obtain stockholder approval for equity compensation plans and significant issuances of equity securities to related parties and for when such issuances represent more than 20&nbsp;percent of an issuer&#146;s
voting power. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Finally, although the proposal purports to relate to special meetings, the supporting statement suggests that the
proposal is nothing more than a vehicle to discuss the Ecuador litigation and related actions against Chevron. The proponent implies that special meetings are an appropriate vehicle for pressuring the Company to succumb to the demands in the Ecuador
litigation and pay a judgment secured through fraud and deceit. Your Board believes that the Ecuador litigation is illegitimate and the product of fraud. In this regard, stockholders should be aware that as part of a nearly 500-page opinion issued
on March&nbsp;4, 2014, Judge Lewis&nbsp;A. Kaplan of the U.S. District Court for the Southern District of New York summarized the court&#146;s factual findings as follows:
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="83%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="9%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">&#147;[Donziger] and the Ecuadorian lawyers he led corrupted the Lago Agrio case. They submitted fraudulent evidence. They coerced one
judge, first to use a court-appointed, supposedly impartial &#145;global expert&#146; to make an overall damages assessment and then to appoint to that important role a man whom Donziger hand-picked and paid to &#145;totally play ball&#146; with the
Lago Agrio plaintiffs. They then paid a Colorado consulting firm secretly to write all or most of the global expert&#146;s report, falsely presented the report as the work of the court-appointed and supposedly impartial expert, and told half-truths
or worse to U.S. courts in attempts to prevent exposure of that and other wrongdoing. Ultimately, the [Lago Agrio Plaintiffs] team wrote the Lago Agrio court&#146;s judgment themselves and promised $500,000 to the Ecuadorian judge to rule in their
favor and sign their judgment. If ever there were a case warranting equitable relief with respect to a judgment procured by fraud, this is it.&#148;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">On August&nbsp;8, 2016, this 500-page trial court opinion was unanimously affirmed on appeal. The
appeals court stated that there was &#147;no basis for dismissal or reversal&#148; of the district court&#146;s judgment, noting that &#147;the record in the present case reveals a parade of corrupt actions by the [Lago Agrio Plaintiffs&#146;] legal
team, including coercion, fraud and bribery, culminating in the promise to Judge Zambrano of $500,000 from a judgment in favor of the [Lago Agrio Plaintiffs].&#148; </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">In addition to the Second Circuit&#146;s opinion, two public prosecutors in South America have now issued opinions against enforcement
of the Ecuadorian judgment.&nbsp;On May&nbsp;13, 2015, the public prosecutor in Brazil issued a nonbinding opinion recommending to the Brazilian Superior Court of Justice that it reject the Ecuadorian plaintiffs&#146; recognition and enforcement
request, finding, among other things, that the Ecuadorian judgment was procured through fraud and corruption and cannot be recognized because it violates Brazilian and international public order.&nbsp;Similarly, on April&nbsp;19, 2016, the public
prosecutor in Argentina issued a nonbinding opinion recommending to the Argentine National Court, First Instance, that it reject the Ecuadorian plaintiffs&#146; recognition and enforcement request, finding, among other things, that enforcement of
the Ecuadorian judgment would violate Argentine public polcy. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">On January&nbsp;20, 2017, the Ontario Superior Court of Justice
granted the motions for summary judgment submitted by Chevron Canada Limited and Chevron Corporation, ruling that the two companies are separate legal entities with separate rights and obligations. As a result, the court dismissed the recognition
and enforcement claim against Chevron Canada Limited. Chevron Corporation remains a defendant in the action.</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Your Board expects
Chevron&#146;s management to act in the best interests of the Company&#146;s stockholders and vigorously defend the Company against this fraudulent action. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:6pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Your Board believes that the 2010 stockholder vote to establish a 15&nbsp;percent threshold for special meetings should be respected.
The By-Law then approved by stockholders responds to the essence of the proposal. </P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P></div>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B>Therefore, your Board recommends that you vote AGAINST this proposal.</B> </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:20pt">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="91%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:20pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5e5e5"> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:20pt; font-family:Arial"><B><A NAME="xtoc304635_70"></A>Additional Information</B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:16pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B><A NAME="xtoc304635_71"></A>Notice and Access</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:16pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="justify"><I></I><B><I>Important Notice Regarding the Availability of Proxy Materials for the Stockholder Meeting to Be Held on May&nbsp;31, 2017: </I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="justify"><I></I><B><I>The Notice of 2017 Annual Meeting, 2017 Proxy Statement, and 2016 Annual Report are available at www.proxyvote.com. </I></B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">This year, we are again furnishing Proxy Materials over the Internet to a number of our stockholders under
the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission&#146;s notice and access rules. Many of our stockholders will receive a Notice Regarding the Availability of Proxy Materials (the Notice) in the mail instead of a paper copy of this Proxy Statement, a
proxy card or voting instruction card, and our 2016 Annual Report. We believe that this process will conserve natural resources and reduce the costs of printing and distributing our Proxy Materials. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The Notice contains instructions on how to access our Proxy Materials and vote over the Internet at <I>www.proxyvote.com</I> and
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
how stockholders can receive a paper copy of our Proxy Materials, including this Proxy Statement, a proxy card or voting instruction card, and our 2016 Annual Report. At <I>www.proxyvote.com</I>,
stockholders can also request to receive future Proxy Materials in printed form by mail or electronically by&nbsp;email. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">All stockholders who do not
receive a Notice will receive a paper copy of the Proxy Materials by mail unless they have previously elected to receive Proxy Materials by email. <FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial"><B>We remind stockholders who receive a Notice that the Notice is not
itself a proxy card and should not be returned with voting instructions.</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial"> </FONT></P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:24pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><A NAME="xtoc304635_72"></A><B>Method and Cost of Soliciting and Tabulating Votes</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:16pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Chevron will bear the costs of soliciting proxies and tabulating your votes. Proxies may be solicited by
mail, Notice and Access (described in Notice and Access, above), email, telephone, or other means. Chevron has retained Broadridge Financial Solutions, Inc., to assist in distributing these Proxy Materials. Alliance Advisors LLC will act as our
proxy solicitor in soliciting votes at an estimated cost of $30,000 plus additional fees for telephone and other solicitation of proxies, if needed, and its reasonable out-of-pocket expenses. Chevron employees may solicit your votes without
additional compensation. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Chevron will reimburse banks, brokers, and other holders of
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
record for reasonable, out-of-pocket expenses for forwarding these Proxy Materials to you, according to certain regulatory fee schedules. We estimate that this reimbursement will cost Chevron
approximately $2 million. The actual amount will depend on variables such as the number of proxy packages mailed, the number of stockholders receiving electronic delivery, and postage costs. See &#147;Email Delivery of Future Proxy Materials&#148;
in this section for&nbsp;information on how you can help reduce printing and mailing&nbsp;costs. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Broadridge Financial Solutions, Inc., will be the
proxy tabulator, and CT Hagberg LLC will act as the Inspector of Election. </P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:24pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><A NAME="xtoc304635_73"></A><B>Householding Information</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:16pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">We have adopted a procedure, approved by the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission, called
&#147;householding.&#148; Under this procedure, stockholders of record who have the same address and last name and receive hard copies of our Proxy Materials will receive only one copy, unless we are notified that one or more of these stockholders
wishes to continue receiving individual copies. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Householding conserves natural resources and reduces our printing and mailing costs. Stockholders who
participate in householding will continue to receive separate proxy cards. Also, householding will not in any way affect dividend check mailings. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">If
you and another stockholder of record with whom you share an address are receiving multiple copies of our Proxy Materials, you can request to participate in householding and receive a single
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
copy of our Proxy Materials in the future by calling Broadridge Financial Solutions, Inc., toll-free at 1-866-540-7095 or by writing to Broadridge Financial Solutions, Inc., Attn: Householding
Department, 51 Mercedes Way, Edgewood, NY 11717. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Alternatively, if you and another stockholder of record with whom you share an address participate
in householding and you wish to receive an individual copy of our Proxy Materials now or discontinue your future participation in householding, please contact Broadridge Financial Solutions, Inc., as indicated above. Proxy Materials will be
delivered promptly and free of charge. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">If you are a street name stockholder, you can request information about householding from your bank, broker,
or other holder of record through which you own your shares. </P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><A NAME="xtoc304635_74"></A><B>Email Delivery of Future Proxy Materials</B>
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:16pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">You can elect to receive future Proxy Materials by email, which will save us the cost of producing and mailing documents to you, by enrolling
at <I>www.icsdelivery.com/cvx</I>. If you choose to receive future Proxy Materials by email, you will receive an email with instructions containing a link to the website where those materials are available and where you can vote. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><A NAME="xtoc304635_75"></A><B>Stockholder of Record Account Maintenance</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:16pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Chevron engages a transfer agent, Computershare, to assist the Company in maintaining the accounts of
individuals and entities that hold Chevron common stock in their own name on the records of the Company, sometimes referred to as &#147;stockholders of record&#148; or &#147;registered stockholders.&#148; All communications concerning accounts of
stockholders of record, including name and address changes, requirements to transfer shares and similar matters, may be handled by calling Computershare&#146;s toll-free number, 1-800-368-8357, or by contacting Computershare through its website at
<I>www.computershare.com/investor</I>. You may also address correspondence to Computershare at
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:2%; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">
P.O. Box 505000, Louisville, KY 40233-5000 or, if by overnight delivery, 462 South 4th Street, Suite 1600, Louisville, KY 40202. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">The Computershare Investment Plan provides interested investors with an alternative for purchasing and selling shares of Chevron common stock and with the
ability to enroll&nbsp;in&nbsp;dividend reinvestment. Additional information is available on Computershare&#146;s website at <I>www.computershare.com/investor</I>. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">If you are a street name stockholder, you may contact your bank, broker, or other holder of record with questions concerning your account.
</P></DIV><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:24pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><A NAME="xtoc304635_76"></A><B>Submission of Stockholder Proposals for 2018 Annual Meeting</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:16pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Arial"><B>Proposals for Inclusion in Next Year&#146;s Proxy Statement (SEC Rule 14a-8) </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">SEC Rule 14a-8 permits stockholders to submit proposals for inclusion in our Proxy Statement if the stockholders and the proposals meet certain
requirements specified in that rule. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

accordance with SEC Rule 14a-8 must be received at our principal executive offices no later than the close of business on December&nbsp;12, 2017. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

required by SEC Rule 14a-8. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="justify"><B>Director Nominees for Inclusion in Next Year&#146;s Proxy Statement (Proxy Access) </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Article IV, Section&nbsp;7 of our By-Laws permits a stockholder or group of stockholders (up to 20) who have owned at least three percent of Chevron
common stock for at least three years to submit director nominees (up to the greater of two nominees or 20 percent of the Board) for inclusion in our Proxy Statement if the nominating stockholder(s) satisfies the requirements specified in our
By-Laws.&nbsp;Additional information about these proxy access requirements can be found in our By-Laws, available at <I>www.chevron.com</I>. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:Arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993"><B><A NAME="xtoc304635_77"></A>Preregistering for and Attending the Annual
Meeting</B> </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:16pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="justify"><B>The Annual Meeting will be held on Wednesday, May&nbsp;31, 2017, at Chevron U.S.A., Inc., 6301 Deauville Boulevard, Midland,
TX 79706. The meeting will begin promptly at 8:00 a.m. CDT. </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt; padding-right:2pt" BGCOLOR="#dee3ee"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="center"><B>Important Notice Regarding Admission to the
2017 Annual Meeting</B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.63em; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Stockholders or their
legal proxy holders who wish to attend the Annual Meeting must preregister with and obtain an admission ticket from Chevron&#146;s Corporate Governance Department. Tickets will be distributed on a first-come, first-served basis. Requests for
admission tickets must be received by Chevron no later than 5:00 p.m. PDT on Thursday, May&nbsp;25, 2017. For complete instructions for preregistering and obtaining an admission ticket, please read the information below.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="justify"><B><U>Registration and Rules for Admission</U> </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="justify"><B>Due to space constraints and other security considerations, only stockholders or their legal proxy holders that have preregistered and been issued an
admission ticket may attend the Annual Meeting. We are not able to admit the guests of either stockholders or their legal proxy holders. Stockholders holding shares in a joint account may request tickets to the meeting if they provide proof of joint
ownership and both stockholders follow the admission requirements described below. </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="justify"><B>To preregister for and receive an admission ticket to the
Annual Meeting, please send your request to Chevron&#146;s Corporate Governance Department by: </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

94583-2324. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">If you have questions about the admission process, you may call 1-877-259-1501. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="justify"><B>Requests for preregistration and an admission ticket must be received no later than 5:00 p.m. PDT on Thursday, May&nbsp;25, 2017. </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="justify"><B>Your request must include your name, email address, mailing address, telephone number (in case we need to contact you regarding your request), and one
of the following: </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
