<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial"><B>If you are a stockholder of record (i.e., you hold your shares through Chevron&#146;s
transfer agent, Computershare),</B></FONT> your request must include one of the following items: (i)&nbsp;a copy of your proxy card delivered as part of your Proxy Materials, (ii)&nbsp;a copy of your Computershare account statement indicating your
ownership of Chevron common stock as of the record date, or (iii)&nbsp;the Notice Regarding the Availability of Proxy Materials, if you received one. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD WIDTH="3%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial"><B>If you are a street name stockholder (i.e., you hold your shares through an
intermediary, such as a bank or broker),</B></FONT> your request must include one of the following items: (i)&nbsp;a copy of the voting instruction form provided by your broker or other holder of record as part of your Proxy Materials, (ii)&nbsp;a
copy of a recent bank or brokerage account statement indicating your ownership of Chevron common stock as of the record date, or (iii)&nbsp;the Notice Regarding the Availability of Proxy Materials, if you received one. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="3%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial"><B>If you are not a stockholder, but are attending as proxy for a stockholder,</B></FONT>
your request must include&nbsp;a valid legal proxy. If you plan to attend as proxy for a stockholder of record, you must present a valid legal proxy from the stockholder of record to you. If you plan to attend as proxy for a street name stockholder,
you must present a valid legal proxy from the stockholder of record (i.e., the bank, broker, or other holder of record) to the street name stockholder that is assignable and a valid legal proxy from the street name stockholder to you. Stockholders
may appoint only one proxy holder to attend on their behalf. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial"><B>Registration requests will be
filled on a first-come,</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial"><B> first-served basis</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial">. If space is available, you will receive an admission ticket by email or mail. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Arial"><B>On the day of the Annual Meeting, please be prepared to present a form of government-issued photo identification, along
with your admission ticket, at the meeting registration desk.</B></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial"> The registration desk will open at 7:00 a.m. CDT on May&nbsp;31, 2017. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Arial" ALIGN="justify"><B><U>Prohibited Items</U> </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Cameras, recording
equipment, electronic devices (including cell phones, tablets, laptops, etc.), purses, bags, briefcases, posters, signs, or packages will NOT be allowed into the Annual Meeting, other than for Company purposes. A checkroom or station for such items
will be provided. We reserve the right to deny admission to any person carrying any item that may pose a threat to the physical safety of stockholders or other meeting participants. Attendees will be asked to pass through a security screening device
prior to entering the Annual Meeting. We regret any inconvenience this may cause you, and we appreciate your cooperation. We also reserve the right to implement additional security procedures to ensure the safety of the meeting attendees. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:30pt; font-family:arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993">The Chevron Way </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:30pt; font-family:arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993">Getting Results the Right Way </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT
 COLOR="#284993">The Chevron Way explains who we are, what we believe, how we achieve and where we aspire to go. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT COLOR="#284993">It
establishes a common understanding not only for us, but for all who interact with us. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Vision </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">At the heart of The Chevron Way is our vision ... to be <I>the</I> global energy company most admired for its people, partnership and performance. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Enabling Human Progress </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">We develop the energy that
improves lives and powers the world forward.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:8pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="51%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="47%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993">Values</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT COLOR="#284993">Our Company&#146;s foundation is on our values, which distinguish us and guide our actions to delivery results. We conduct our
business in a socially and environmentally responsible manner, respecting the law and universal human rights to benefit the communities where we work.</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993">Diversity and Inclusion</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">We learn from and respect the cultures in which we operate. We have an inclusive work environment that values the uniqueness and diversity of individual
talents, experiences and ideas.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993">High Performance</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">We are passionate about delivering results, and strive to continually improve. We
hold ourselves accountable for our actions and outcomes. We apply proven processes in a fit-for-purpose manner and always look for innovative and agile solutions.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993">Integrity and Trust</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">We are honest with ourselves and others, and honor our commitments. We trust, respect and support each other. We earn the trust of our colleagues and
partners by operating with the highest ethical standards in all we do.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><FONT
 COLOR="#284993">Partnership</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">We build trusting and mutually beneficial
relationship by collaborating with our communities, governments, customers, suppliers and other business partners. We are most successful when our partners succeed with us.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993">Protecting People and the Environment</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">We place the highest priority on the health and safety of our workforce and
protection of our assets, communities and the environment. We deliver world-class performance with a focus on preventing high-consequence incidents.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993">Strategies</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><FONT
 COLOR="#284993">Our strategies guide our actions to deliver industry-leading results and superior shareholder value in any business environment.</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993">Enterprise Strategies</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">People</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Invest in people to develop and empower a highly
competent workforce that delivers results the right way</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Execution</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Deliver results through disciplined
operational excellence, capital stewardship and cost efficiency</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Growth</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Grow profits and returns by using our
competitive advantages</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Technology and Functional Excellence</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Differentiate performance through technology and functional expertise</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><FONT COLOR="#284993">Major Business Strategies</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Upstream</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Deliver industry-leading returns while developing high-value resource opportunities</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Downstream &amp; Chemicals</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Grow earnings across the value chain and make targeted investments to lead the industry in returns</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Midstream</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">Deliver operational, commercial and technical expertise to enhance results in Upstream and Downstream &amp; Chemicals</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify">For more information: The Chevron Way</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="justify"><I><FONT COLOR="#284993">www.chevron.com/about/the-chevron-way</FONT></I></P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>24 Hours a Day, 7 Days a Week</B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Use the Internet to transmit your voting instructions and for electronic delivery of
information up until 11:59 p.m. Eastern Time the day before the meeting date or on the applicable Employee Voting Plan cutoff date. Have your proxy card in hand when you access the website and then follow the instructions to obtain your records and
to create an electronic voting instruction form.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>VOTE BY PHONE - <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">1-800-690-6903</FONT></FONT></FONT></B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Use any touch-tone
telephone to transmit your voting instructions up until 11:59 p.m. Eastern Time<B> </B>the day before the meeting date or on the applicable Employee Voting Plan cutoff date. Have your proxy card in hand when you call and then follow the
instructions.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>VOTE BY MAIL</B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Mark, sign, and date your proxy card and return it in the postage-paid envelope we have provided or return it to Chevron Corporation, c/o Broadridge, 51
Mercedes Way, Edgewood, NY 11717.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>ELECTRONIC DELIVERY OF FUTURE STOCKHOLDER
COMMUNICATIONS</B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Times New Roman">If you would like to reduce the costs incurred by Chevron Corporation in mailing proxy materials, you can consent to receiving all future
proxy statements, proxy cards, and annual reports electronically via <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">e-mail</FONT> or the Internet. To sign up for electronic delivery, please follow the instructions above to vote using the Internet and, when
prompted, indicate that you agree to receive or access stockholder communications electronically in future years.</P></TD>

<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="7"><FONT STYLE="font-size:8pt">Dear Stockholder:</FONT></TD>

<TD VALIGN="top"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="7"> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The lower portion of this form is your proxy card for voting
at Chevron Corporation&#146;s 2017 Annual Meeting of Stockholders. It is important that you vote. You may vote by telephone, Internet, or mail by following the instructions printed on this form. If you vote by mail, please mark, sign, date, and
return the proxy card (the lower portion of this form) using the enclosed postage-paid envelope or return it to Chevron Corporation, c/o Broadridge, 51 Mercedes Way, Edgewood, NY 11717. <B>You must sign, date, and return the proxy card for your vote
to be counted. </B></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD></TR>

<TD HEIGHT="5"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="7" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-size:8pt"><B><U>Important Notice Regarding Admission to the 2017 Annual Meeting</U></B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="7"><FONT STYLE="font-size:8pt">Stockholders or their legal proxy holders who wish to attend the Annual Meeting must preregister with and obtain an admission ticket from Chevron&#146;s Corporate Governance Department.
Tickets will be distributed on a first-come, first-served basis. Requests for admission tickets must be received by Chevron no later than 5:00 p.m. PDT on Thursday, May&nbsp;25, 2017. For complete instructions for preregistering and obtaining an
admission ticket, see page 81 of the Proxy Statement.</FONT></TD>

S. Watson, R. Hewitt Pate, and Mary A. Francis, and each of them, proxy holders of the undersigned, each with full power of substitution, to represent and to vote all the shares of<B> </B>Chevron Corporation common stock held of record by the
undersigned on Monday, April&nbsp;3, 2017 at Chevron Corporation&#146;s<B> </B>Annual Meeting of Stockholders, to be held on Wednesday, May&nbsp;31, 2017, and any adjournment or postponement thereof. The proxy holders will vote as directed by the
undersigned. <B>If the undersigned signs, dates, and returns this proxy card but gives no directions for voting, the proxy holders will vote in accordance with the Board&#146;s recommendations. The proxy holders will vote in accordance with their
discretion on such other matters as may properly come before the meeting and any adjournment or postponement thereof, including, without limitation, any proposal to adjourn the meeting to a later time and place for the purpose of soliciting
additional proxies, unless the undersigned strikes out this sentence.</B></P></TD>

accordance with the instructions given herein, at Chevron Corporation&#146;s Annual Meeting of Stockholders and any adjournment or postponement thereof, on all matters properly coming before the meeting, including but not limited to the matters set
forth on the reverse side. If the undersigned has shares in an Employee Voting Plan and does not vote those shares, the Employee Voting Plan fiduciary may or may not vote the shares, in accordance with the terms of the Employee Voting Plan. <B>All
votes of Employee Voting Plan shares must be received by the respective fiduciary by 11:59 P.M., EDT, Thursday, May&nbsp;25, 2017, or other Employee Voting Plan cutoff date determined by the Employee Voting Plan fiduciary, in order to be counted.
